  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: bd3f8ba6a2445b646991a3e44f7f687a, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  And Solomon the son of David was strengthened in his kingdom, and
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God <i>was</i> with him, and magnified
        him exceedingly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Solomon spake unto all Israel, to the captains of thousands
        and of hundreds, and to the judges, and to every governor in all Israel,
        the chief of the fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Solomon, and all the congregation with him, went to the high place
        that <i>was</i> at Gibeon; for there was the tabernacle of the congregation
        of God, which Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had made
        in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the ark of God had David brought up from Kirjath-jearim to <i>the
        place which</i> David had prepared for it: for he had pitched a tent for
        it at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Moreover the brasen altar, that Bezaleel the son of Uri, the son
        of Hur, had made, he put before the tabernacle of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        and Solomon and the congregation sought unto it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Solomon went up thither to the brasen altar before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        which <i>was</i> at the tabernacle of the congregation, and offered a thousand
        burnt offerings upon it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In that night did God appear unto Solomon, and said unto him, Ask
        what I shall give thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Solomon said unto God, Thou hast shewed great mercy unto David
        my father, and hast made me to reign in his stead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God, let thy promise unto David
        my father be established: for thou hast made me king over a people like the
        dust of the earth in multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Give me now wisdom and knowledge, that I may go out and come in before
        this people: for who can judge this thy people, <i>that is so</i> great? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And God said to Solomon, Because this was in thine heart, and thou
        hast not asked riches, wealth, or honour, nor the life of thine enemies,
        neither yet hast asked long life; but hast asked wisdom and knowledge for
        thyself, that thou mayest judge my people, over whom I have made thee king: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'wisdom and knowledge <i>is</i> granted unto thee; and I will give
        thee riches, and wealth, and honour, such as none of the kings have had that
        <i>have been</i> before thee, neither shall there any after thee have the
        like. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Solomon came <i>from his journey</i> to the high place that
        <i>was</i> at Gibeon to Jerusalem, from before the tabernacle of the congregation,
        and reigned over Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Solomon gathered chariots and horsemen: and he had a thousand
        and four hundred chariots, and twelve thousand horsemen, which he placed
        in the chariot cities, and with the king at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the king made silver and gold at Jerusalem <i>as plenteous</i>
        as stones, and cedar trees made he as the sycomore trees that <i>are</i>
        in the vale for abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Solomon had horses brought out of Egypt, and linen yarn: the
        king''s merchants received the linen yarn at a price. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they fetched up, and brought forth out of Egypt a chariot for
        six hundred <i>shekels</i> of silver, and an horse for an hundred and fifty:
        and so brought they out <i>horses</i> for all the kings of the Hittites,
        and for the kings of Syria, by their means.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Building the Temple'
      title: Building the Temple
      number: 1
      content: '  And Solomon determined to build an house for the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and an house for his kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Solomon told out threescore and ten thousand men to bear burdens,
        and fourscore thousand to hew in the mountain, and three thousand and six
        hundred to oversee them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Solomon sent to Huram the king of Tyre, saying, As thou didst
        deal with David my father, and didst send him cedars to build him an house
        to dwell therein, <i>even so deal with me</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, I build an house to the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        my God, to dedicate <i>it</i> to him, <i>and</i> to burn before him sweet
        incense, and for the continual shewbread, and for the burnt offerings morning
        and evening, on the sabbaths, and on the new moons, and on the solemn feasts
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> our God. This <i>is an ordinance</i> for
        ever to Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the house which I build <i>is</i> great: for great <i>is</i>
        our God above all gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But who is able to build him an house, seeing the heaven and heaven
        of heavens cannot contain him? who <i>am</i> I then, that I should build
        him an house, save only to burn sacrifice before him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Send me now therefore a man cunning to work in gold, and in silver,
        and in brass, and in iron, and in purple, and crimson, and blue, and that
        can skill to grave with the cunning men that <i>are</i> with me in Judah
        and in Jerusalem, whom David my father did provide. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Send me also cedar trees, fir trees, and algum trees, out of Lebanon:
        for I know that thy servants can skill to cut timber in Lebanon; and, behold,
        my servants <i>shall be</i> with thy servants, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'even to prepare me timber in abundance: for the house which I am
        about to build <i>shall be</i> wonderful great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And, behold, I will give to thy servants, the hewers that cut timber,
        twenty thousand measures of beaten wheat, and twenty thousand measures of
        barley, and twenty thousand baths of wine, and twenty thousand baths of oil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Huram the king of Tyre answered in writing, which he sent to
        Solomon, Because the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath loved his people, he
        hath made thee king over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Huram said moreover, Blessed <i>be</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel, that made heaven and earth, who hath given to David the king
        a wise son, endued with prudence and understanding, that might build an house
        for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and an house for his kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And now I have sent a cunning man, endued with understanding, of
        Huram my father''s, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the son of a woman of the daughters of Dan, and his father <i>was</i>
        a man of Tyre, skilful to work in gold, and in silver, in brass, in iron,
        in stone, and in timber, in purple, in blue, and in fine linen, and in crimson;
        also to grave any manner of graving, and to find out every device which shall
        be put to him, with thy cunning men, and with the cunning men of my lord
        David thy father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now therefore the wheat, and the barley, the oil, and the wine, which
        my lord hath spoken of, let him send unto his servants: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Foreign Labour'
      title: Foreign Labour
      number: 16
      content: 'and we will cut wood out of Lebanon, as much as thou shalt need:
        and we will bring it to thee in floats by sea to Joppa; and thou shalt carry
        it up to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Solomon numbered all the strangers that <i>were</i> in the land
        of Israel, after the numbering wherewith David his father had numbered them;
        and they were found an hundred and fifty thousand and three thousand and
        six hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And he set threescore and ten thousand of them <i>to be</i> bearers
        of burdens, and fourscore thousand <i>to be</i> hewers in the mountain, and
        three thousand and six hundred overseers to set the people a work.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Temple Building'
      title: The Temple Building
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Solomon began to build the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        at Jerusalem in mount Moriah, where <i>the </i><smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        appeared unto David his father, in the place that David had prepared in the
        threshingfloor of Ornan the Jebusite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he began to build in the second <i>day</i> of the second month,
        in the fourth year of his reign.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now these <i>are the things wherein</i> Solomon was instructed for
        the building of the house of God. The length by cubits after the first measure
        <i>was</i> threescore cubits, and the breadth twenty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the porch that <i>was</i> in the front <i>of the house</i>, the
        length <i>of it was</i> according to the breadth of the house, twenty cubits,
        and the height <i>was</i> an hundred and twenty: and he overlaid it within
        with pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the greater house he cieled with fir tree, which he overlaid
        with fine gold, and set thereon palm trees and chains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he garnished the house with precious stones for beauty: and the
        gold <i>was</i> gold of Parvaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He overlaid also the house, the beams, the posts, and the walls thereof,
        and the doors thereof, with gold; and graved cherubims on the walls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he made the most holy house, the length whereof <i>was</i> according
        to the breadth of the house, twenty cubits, and the breadth thereof twenty
        cubits: and he overlaid it with fine gold, <i>amounting</i> to six hundred
        talents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the weight of the nails <i>was</i> fifty shekels of gold. And
        he overlaid the upper chambers with gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And in the most holy house he made two cherubims of image work, and
        overlaid them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the wings of the cherubims <i>were</i> twenty cubits long: one
        wing <i>of the one cherub was</i> five cubits, reaching to the wall of the
        house: and the other wing <i>was likewise</i> five cubits, reaching to the
        wing of the other cherub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And <i>one</i> wing of the other cherub <i>was</i> five cubits, reaching
        to the wall of the house: and the other wing <i>was</i> five cubits <i>also</i>,
        joining to the wing of the other cherub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The wings of these cherubims spread themselves forth twenty cubits:
        and they stood on their feet, and their faces <i>were</i> inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he made the vail <i>of</i> blue, and purple, and crimson, and
        fine linen, and wrought cherubims thereon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Also he made before the house two pillars of thirty and five cubits
        high, and the chapiter that <i>was</i> on the top of each of them <i>was</i>
        five cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he made chains, <i>as</i> in the oracle, and put <i>them</i>
        on the heads of the pillars; and made an hundred pomegranates, and put <i>them</i>
        on the chains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And he reared up the pillars before the temple, one on the right hand,
        and the other on the left; and called the name of that on the right hand
        Jachin, and the name of that on the left Boaz.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Temple Furniture'
      title: Temple Furniture
      number: 1
      content: '  Moreover he made an altar of brass, twenty cubits the length thereof,
        and twenty cubits the breadth thereof, and ten cubits the height thereof.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Also he made a molten sea of ten cubits from brim to brim, round
        in compass, and five cubits the height thereof; and a line of thirty cubits
        did compass it round about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And under it <i>was</i> the similitude of oxen, which did compass
        it round about: ten in a cubit, compassing the sea round about. Two rows
        of oxen <i>were</i> cast, when it was cast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'It stood upon twelve oxen, three looking toward the north, and three
        looking toward the west, and three looking toward the south, and three looking
        toward the east: and the sea <i>was set</i> above upon them, and all their
        hinder parts <i>were inward</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the thickness of it <i>was</i> an handbreadth, and the brim of
        it like the work of the brim of a cup, with flowers of lilies; <i>and</i>
        it received and held three thousand baths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He made also ten lavers, and put five on the right hand, and five
        on the left, to wash in them: such things as they offered for the burnt offering
        they washed in them; but the sea <i>was</i> for the priests to wash in.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he made ten candlesticks of gold according to their form, and
        set <i>them</i> in the temple, five on the right hand, and five on the left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He made also ten tables, and placed <i>them</i> in the temple, five
        on the right side, and five on the left. And he made an hundred basons of
        gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Furthermore he made the court of the priests, and the great court,
        and doors for the court, and overlaid the doors of them with brass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he set the sea on the right side of the east end, over against
        the south. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Huram made the pots, and the shovels, and the basons.And Huram
        finished the work that he was to make for king Solomon for the house of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<i>to wit</i>, the two pillars, and the pommels, and the chapiters
        <i>which were</i> on the top of the two pillars, and the two wreaths to cover
        the two pommels of the chapiters which <i>were</i> on the top of the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and four hundred pomegranates on the two wreaths; two rows of pomegranates
        on each wreath, to cover the two pommels of the chapiters which <i>were</i>
        upon the pillars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He made also bases, and lavers made he upon the bases; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'one sea, and twelve oxen under it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The pots also, and the shovels, and the fleshhooks, and all their
        instruments, did Huram his father make to king Solomon for the house of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of bright brass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In the plain of Jordan did the king cast them, in the clay ground
        between Succoth and Zeredathah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Thus Solomon made all these vessels in great abundance: for the weight
        of the brass could not be found out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Solomon made all the vessels that <i>were for</i> the house of
        God, the golden altar also, and the tables whereon the shewbread <i>was set</i>; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'moreover the candlesticks with their lamps, that they should burn
        after the manner before the oracle, of pure gold; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and the flowers, and the lamps, and the tongs, <i>made he of</i>
        gold, <i>and</i> that perfect gold; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and the snuffers, and the basons, and the spoons, and the censers,
        <i>of</i> pure gold: and the entry of the house, the inner doors thereof
        for the most holy <i>place</i>, and the doors of the house of the temple,
        <i>were of</i> gold.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Dedication'
      title: The Dedication
      number: 1
      content: '  Thus all the work that Solomon made for the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        was finished: and Solomon brought in <i>all</i> the things that David his
        father had dedicated; and the silver, and the gold, and all the instruments,
        put he among the treasures of the house of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Solomon assembled the elders of Israel, and all the heads of
        the tribes, the chief of the fathers of the children of Israel, unto Jerusalem,
        to bring up the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> out
        of the city of David, which <i>is</i> Zion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Wherefore all the men of Israel assembled themselves unto the king
        in the feast which <i>was</i> in the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And all the elders of Israel came; and the Levites took up the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And they brought up the ark, and the tabernacle of the congregation,
        and all the holy vessels that <i>were</i> in the tabernacle, these did the
        priests <i>and</i> the Levites bring up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Also king Solomon, and all the congregation of Israel that were assembled
        unto him before the ark, sacrificed sheep and oxen, which could not be told
        nor numbered for multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the priests brought in the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        unto his place, to the oracle of the house, into the most holy <i>place,
        even</i> under the wings of the cherubims: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'for the cherubims spread forth <i>their</i> wings over the place
        of the ark, and the cherubims covered the ark and the staves thereof above. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they drew out the staves <i>of the ark</i>, that the ends of
        the staves were seen from the ark before the oracle; but they were not seen
        without. And there it is unto this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<i>There was</i> nothing in the ark save the two tables which Moses
        put <i>therein</i> at Horeb, when the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> made <i>a
        covenant</i> with the children of Israel, when they came out of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it came to pass, when the priests were come out of the holy <i>place:</i>
        (for all the priests <i>that were</i> present were sanctified, <i>and</i>
        did not <i>then</i> wait by course: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'also the Levites <i>which were</i> the singers, all of them of Asaph,
        of Heman, of Jeduthun, with their sons and their brethren, <i>being</i> arrayed
        in white linen, having cymbals and psalteries and harps, stood at the east
        end of the altar, and with them an hundred and twenty priests sounding with
        trumpets:) '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'it came even to pass, as the trumpeters and singers <i>were</i> as
        one, to make one sound to be heard in praising and thanking the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        and when they lifted up <i>their</i> voice with the trumpets and cymbals
        and instruments of musick, and praised the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, <i>saying</i>,
        For <i>he is</i> good; for his mercy <i>endureth</i> for ever: that <i>then</i>
        the house was filled with a cloud, <i>even</i> the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'so that the priests could not stand to minister by reason of the
        cloud: for the glory of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had filled the house
        of God.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Then said Solomon, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath said that
        he would dwell in the thick darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But I have built an house of habitation for thee, and a place for
        thy dwelling for ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the king turned his face, and blessed the whole congregation
        of Israel: and all the congregation of Israel stood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he said, Blessed <i>be</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God
        of Israel, who hath with his hands fulfilled <i>that</i> which he spake with
        his mouth to my father David, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Since the day that I brought forth my people out of the land of Egypt
        I chose no city among all the tribes of Israel to build an house in, that
        my name might be there; neither chose I any man to be a ruler over my people
        Israel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'but I have chosen Jerusalem, that my name might be there; and have
        chosen David to be over my people Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now it was in the heart of David my father to build an house for
        the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said to David my father, Forasmuch
        as it was in thine heart to build an house for my name, thou didst well in
        that it was in thine heart: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'notwithstanding thou shalt not build the house; but thy son which
        shall come forth out of thy loins, he shall build the house for my name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> therefore hath performed his word
        that he hath spoken: for I am risen up in the room of David my father, and
        am set on the throne of Israel, as the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> promised,
        and have built the house for the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Solomon''s Prayer'
      title: Solomon's Prayer
      number: 11
      content: 'And in it have I put the ark, wherein <i>is</i> the covenant of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, that he made with the children of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he stood before the altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        in the presence of all the congregation of Israel, and spread forth his hands: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for Solomon had made a brasen scaffold, of five cubits long, and
        five cubits broad, and three cubits high, and had set it in the midst of
        the court: and upon it he stood, and kneeled down upon his knees before all
        the congregation of Israel, and spread forth his hands toward heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and said, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel, <i>there is</i>
        no God like thee in the heaven, nor in the earth; which keepest covenant,
        and <i>shewest</i> mercy unto thy servants, that walk before thee with all
        their hearts: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'thou which hast kept with thy servant David my father that which
        thou hast promised him; and spakest with thy mouth, and hast fulfilled <i>it</i>
        with thine hand, as <i>it is</i> this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now therefore, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel, keep
        with thy servant David my father that which thou hast promised him, saying,
        There shall not fail thee a man in my sight to sit upon the throne of Israel;
        yet so that thy children take heed to their way to walk in my law, as thou
        hast walked before me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now then, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel, let thy word
        be verified, which thou hast spoken unto thy servant David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But will God in very deed dwell with men on the earth? Behold, heaven
        and the heaven of heavens cannot contain thee; how much less this house which
        I have built! '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Have respect therefore to the prayer of thy servant, and to his supplication,
        O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> my God, to hearken unto the cry and the prayer
        which thy servant prayeth before thee: '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'that thine eyes may be open upon this house day and night, upon the
        place whereof thou hast said that thou wouldest put thy name there; to hearken
        unto the prayer which thy servant prayeth toward this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Hearken therefore unto the supplications of thy servant, and of thy
        people Israel, which they shall make toward this place: hear thou from thy
        dwelling place, <i>even</i> from heaven; and when thou hearest, forgive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'If a man sin against his neighbour, and an oath be laid upon him
        to make him swear, and the oath come before thine altar in this house; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'then hear thou from heaven, and do, and judge thy servants, by requiting
        the wicked, by recompensing his way upon his own head; and by justifying
        the righteous, by giving him according to his righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And if thy people Israel be put to the worse before the enemy, because
        they have sinned against thee; and shall return and confess thy name, and
        pray and make supplication before thee in this house; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then hear thou from the heavens, and forgive the sin of thy people
        Israel, and bring them again unto the land which thou gavest to them and
        to their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When the heaven is shut up, and there is no rain, because they have
        sinned against thee; <i>yet</i> if they pray toward this place, and confess
        thy name, and turn from their sin, when thou dost afflict them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'then hear thou from heaven, and forgive the sin of thy servants,
        and of thy people Israel, when thou hast taught them the good way, wherein
        they should walk; and send rain upon thy land, which thou hast given unto
        thy people for an inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'If there be dearth in the land, if there be pestilence, if there
        be blasting, or mildew, locusts, or caterpillers; if their enemies besiege
        them in the cities of their land; whatsoever sore or whatsoever sickness
        <i>there be:</i>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<i>then</i> what prayer <i>or</i> what supplication soever shall
        be made of any man, or of all thy people Israel, when every one shall know
        his own sore and his own grief, and shall spread forth his hands in this
        house: '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'then hear thou from heaven thy dwelling place, and forgive, and render
        unto every man according unto all his ways, whose heart thou knowest; (for
        thou only knowest the hearts of the children of men:) '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'that they may fear thee, to walk in thy ways, so long as they live
        in the land which thou gavest unto our fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Moreover concerning the stranger, which is not of thy people Israel,
        but is come from a far country for thy great name''s sake, and thy mighty
        hand, and thy stretched out arm; if they come and pray in this house; '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'then hear thou from the heavens, <i>even</i> from thy dwelling place,
        and do according to all that the stranger calleth to thee for; that all people
        of the earth may know thy name, and fear thee, as <i>doth</i> thy people
        Israel, and may know that this house which I have built is called by thy
        name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'If thy people go out to war against their enemies by the way that
        thou shalt send them, and they pray unto thee toward this city which thou
        hast chosen, and the house which I have built for thy name; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'then hear thou from the heavens their prayer and their supplication,
        and maintain their cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'If they sin against thee, (for <i>there is</i> no man which sinneth
        not,) and thou be angry with them, and deliver them over before <i>their</i>
        enemies, and they carry them away captives unto a land far off or near; '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'yet <i>if</i> they bethink themselves in the land whither they are
        carried captive, and turn and pray unto thee in the land of their captivity,
        saying, We have sinned, we have done amiss, and have dealt wickedly; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'if they return to thee with all their heart and with all their soul
        in the land of their captivity, whither they have carried them captives,
        and pray toward their land, which thou gavest unto their fathers, and <i>toward</i>
        the city which thou hast chosen, and toward the house which I have built
        for thy name: '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'then hear thou from the heavens, <i>even</i> from thy dwelling place,
        their prayer and their supplications, and maintain their cause, and forgive
        thy people which have sinned against thee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Now, my God, let, I beseech thee, thine eyes be open, and <i>let</i>
        thine ears <i>be</i> attent unto the prayer <i>that is made</i> in this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Now therefore arise, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God, into thy
        resting place, thou, and the ark of thy strength: let thy priests, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God, be clothed with salvation, and let thy saints rejoice in goodness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God, turn not away the face of thine
        anointed: remember the mercies of David thy servant.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Glory of the Lord'
      title: The Glory of the Lord
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when Solomon had made an end of praying, the fire came down
        from heaven, and consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices; and the
        glory of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> filled the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the priests could not enter into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        because the glory of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had filled the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>''s
        house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when all the children of Israel saw how the fire came down, and
        the glory of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> upon the house, they bowed themselves
        with their faces to the ground upon the pavement, and worshipped, and praised
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, <i>saying</i>, For <i>he is</i> good; for
        his mercy <i>endureth</i> for ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the king and all the people offered sacrifices before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And king Solomon offered a sacrifice of twenty and two thousand oxen,
        and an hundred and twenty thousand sheep: so the king and all the people
        dedicated the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the priests waited on their offices: the Levites also with instruments
        of musick of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which David the king had made
        to praise the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, because his mercy <i>endureth</i>
        for ever, when David praised by their ministry; and the priests sounded trumpets
        before them, and all Israel stood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Moreover Solomon hallowed the middle of the court that <i>was</i>
        before the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: for there he offered
        burnt offerings, and the fat of the peace offerings, because the brasen altar
        which Solomon had made was not able to receive the burnt offerings, and the
        meat offerings, and the fat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Also at the same time Solomon kept the feast seven days, and all
        Israel with him, a very great congregation, from the entering in of Hamath
        unto the river of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And in the eighth day they made a solemn assembly: for they kept
        the dedication of the altar seven days, and the feast seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Divine Covenant'
      title: The Divine Covenant
      number: 10
      content: 'And on the three and twentieth day of the seventh month he sent the
        people away into their tents, glad and merry in heart for the goodness that
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had shewed unto David, and to Solomon, and
        to Israel his people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Thus Solomon finished the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and the king''s house: and all that came into Solomon''s heart to make in
        the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and in his own house, he prosperously
        effected. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> appeared to Solomon by night,
        and said unto him, I have heard thy prayer, and have chosen this place to
        myself for an house of sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If I shut up heaven that there be no rain, or if I command the locusts
        to devour the land, or if I send pestilence among my people; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'if my people, which are called by my name, shall humble themselves,
        and pray, and seek my face, and turn from their wicked ways; then will I
        hear from heaven, and will forgive their sin, and will heal their land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now mine eyes shall be open, and mine ears attent unto the prayer
        <i>that is made</i> in this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For now have I chosen and sanctified this house, that my name may
        be there for ever: and mine eyes and mine heart shall be there perpetually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And as for thee, if thou wilt walk before me, as David thy father
        walked, and do according to all that I have commanded thee, and shalt observe
        my statutes and my judgments; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'then will I stablish the throne of thy kingdom, according as I have
        covenanted with David thy father, saying, There shall not fail thee a man
        <i>to be</i> ruler in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But if ye turn away, and forsake my statutes and my commandments,
        which I have set before you, and shall go and serve other gods, and worship
        them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'then will I pluck them up by the roots out of my land which I have
        given them; and this house, which I have sanctified for my name, will I cast
        out of my sight, and will make it <i>to be</i> a proverb and a byword among
        all nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And this house, which is high, shall be an astonishment to every
        one that passeth by it; so that he shall say, Why hath the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        done thus unto this land, and unto this house? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And it shall be answered, Because they forsook the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of their fathers, which brought them forth out of the land of Egypt,
        and laid hold on other gods, and worshipped them, and served them: therefore
        hath he brought all this evil upon them.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon''s Reign'
      title: Solomon's Reign
      number: 1
      content: '  And it came to pass at the end of twenty years, wherein Solomon
        had built the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and his own house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that the cities which Huram had restored to Solomon, Solomon built
        them, and caused the children of Israel to dwell there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Solomon went to Hamath-zobah, and prevailed against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he built Tadmor in the wilderness, and all the store cities,
        which he built in Hamath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Also he built Beth-horon the upper, and Beth-horon the nether, fenced
        cities, with walls, gates, and bars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and Baalath, and all the store cities that Solomon had, and all the
        chariot cities, and the cities of the horsemen, and all that Solomon desired
        to build in Jerusalem, and in Lebanon, and throughout all the land of his
        dominion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  <i>As for</i> all the people <i>that were</i> left of the Hittites,
        and the Amorites, and the Perizzites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites,
        which <i>were</i> not of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<i>but</i> of their children, who were left after them in the land,
        whom the children of Israel consumed not, them did Solomon make to pay tribute
        until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But of the children of Israel did Solomon make no servants for his
        work; but they <i>were</i> men of war, and chief of his captains, and captains
        of his chariots and horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And these <i>were</i> the chief of king Solomon''s officers, <i>even</i>
        two hundred and fifty, that bare rule over the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Solomon brought up the daughter of Pharaoh out of the city of
        David unto the house that he had built for her: for he said, My wife shall
        not dwell in the house of David king of Israel, because <i>the places are</i>
        holy, whereunto the ark of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Solomon offered burnt offerings unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        on the altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which he had built before
        the porch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'even after a certain rate every day, offering according to the commandment
        of Moses, on the sabbaths, and on the new moons, and on the solemn feasts,
        three times in the year, <i>even</i> in the feast of unleavened bread, and
        in the feast of weeks, and in the feast of tabernacles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he appointed, according to the order of David his father, the
        courses of the priests to their service, and the Levites to their charges,
        to praise and minister before the priests, as the duty of every day required:
        the porters also by their courses at every gate: for so had David the man
        of God commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they departed not from the commandment of the king unto the priests
        and Levites concerning any matter, or concerning the treasures.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now all the work of Solomon was prepared unto the day of the foundation
        of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and until it was finished.
        <i>So</i> the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> was perfected.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then went Solomon to Ezion-geber, and to Eloth, at the sea side in
        the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And Huram sent him by the hands of his servants ships, and servants
        that had knowledge of the sea; and they went with the servants of Solomon
        to Ophir, and took thence four hundred and fifty talents of gold, and brought
        <i>them</i> to king Solomon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Queen of Sheba'
      title: The Queen of Sheba
      number: 1
      content: '  And when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon, she came
        to prove Solomon with hard questions at Jerusalem, with a very great company,
        and camels that bare spices, and gold in abundance, and precious stones:
        and when she was come to Solomon, she communed with him of all that was in
        her heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Solomon told her all her questions: and there was nothing hid
        from Solomon which he told her not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when the queen of Sheba had seen the wisdom of Solomon, and the
        house that he had built, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and the meat of his table, and the sitting of his servants, and the
        attendance of his ministers, and their apparel; his cupbearers also, and
        their apparel; and his ascent by which he went up into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        there was no more spirit in her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And she said to the king, <i>It was</i> a true report which I heard
        in mine own land of thine acts, and of thy wisdom: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'howbeit I believed not their words, until I came, and mine eyes had
        seen <i>it:</i> and, behold, the one half of the greatness of thy wisdom
        was not told me: <i>for</i> thou exceedest the fame that I heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Happy <i>are</i> thy men, and happy <i>are</i> these thy servants,
        which stand continually before thee, and hear thy wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Blessed be the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God, which delighted
        in thee to set thee on his throne, <i>to be</i> king for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        thy God: because thy God loved Israel, to establish them for ever, therefore
        made he thee king over them, to do judgment and justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And she gave the king an hundred and twenty talents of gold, and
        of spices great abundance, and precious stones: neither was there any such
        spice as the queen of Sheba gave king Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the servants also of Huram, and the servants of Solomon, which
        brought gold from Ophir, brought algum trees and precious stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the king made <i>of</i> the algum trees terraces to the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and to the king''s palace, and harps
        and psalteries for singers: and there were none such seen before in the land
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Solomon''s Wealth'
      title: Solomon's Wealth
      number: 12
      content: 'And king Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all her desire, whatsoever
        she asked, beside <i>that</i> which she had brought unto the king. So she
        turned, and went away to her own land, she and her servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the weight of gold that came to Solomon in one year was six hundred
        and threescore and six talents of gold; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'beside <i>that which</i> chapmen and merchants brought. And all the
        kings of Arabia and governors of the country brought gold and silver to Solomon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And king Solomon made two hundred targets <i>of</i> beaten gold:
        six hundred <i>shekels</i> of beaten gold went to one target. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And three hundred shields <i>made he of</i> beaten gold: three hundred
        <i>shekels</i> of gold went to one shield. And the king put them in the house
        of the forest of Lebanon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with
        pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And <i>there were</i> six steps to the throne, with a footstool of
        gold, <i>which were</i> fastened to the throne, and stays on each side of
        the sitting place, and two lions standing by the stays: '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and twelve lions stood there on the one side and on the other upon
        the six steps. There was not the like made in any kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And all the drinking vessels of king Solomon <i>were of</i> gold,
        and all the vessels of the house of the forest of Lebanon <i>were of</i>
        pure gold: none <i>were of</i> silver; it was <i>not</i> any thing accounted
        of in the days of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: His Wisdom'
      title: His Wisdom
      number: 21
      content: 'For the king''s ships went to Tarshish with the servants of Huram:
        every three years once came the ships of Tarshish bringing gold, and silver,
        ivory, and apes, and peacocks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And king Solomon passed all the kings of the earth in riches and
        wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And all the kings of the earth sought the presence of Solomon, to
        hear his wisdom, that God had put in his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And they brought every man his present, vessels of silver, and vessels
        of gold, and raiment, harness, and spices, horses, and mules, a rate year
        by year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Solomon had four thousand stalls for horses and chariots, and
        twelve thousand horsemen; whom he bestowed in the chariot cities, and with
        the king at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And he reigned over all the kings from the river even unto the land
        of the Philistines, and to the border of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the king made silver in Jerusalem as stones, and cedar trees
        made he as the sycomore trees that <i>are</i> in the low plains in abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And they brought unto Solomon horses out of Egypt, and out of all
        lands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, first and last, <i>are</i> they
        not written in the book of Nathan the prophet, and in the prophecy of Ahijah
        the Shilonite, and in the visions of Iddo the seer against Jeroboam the son
        of Nebat? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And Solomon slept with his fathers, and he was buried in the city
        of David his father: and Rehoboam his son reigned in his stead.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Kingdom of Judah'
      title: The Kingdom of Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  And Rehoboam went to Shechem: for to Shechem were all Israel come
        to make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who <i>was</i>
        in Egypt, whither he had fled from the presence of Solomon the king, heard
        <i>it</i>, that Jeroboam returned out of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And they sent and called him. So Jeroboam and all Israel came and
        spake to Rehoboam, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thy father made our yoke grievous: now therefore ease thou somewhat
        the grievous servitude of thy father, and his heavy yoke that he put upon
        us, and we will serve thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: King Rehoboam'
      title: King Rehoboam
      number: 5
      content: 'And he said unto them, Come again unto me after three days. And the
        people departed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And king Rehoboam took counsel with the old men that had stood before
        Solomon his father while he yet lived, saying, What counsel give ye <i>me</i>
        to return answer to this people? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they spake unto him, saying, If thou be kind to this people,
        and please them, and speak good words to them, they will be thy servants
        for ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But he forsook the counsel which the old men gave him, and took counsel
        with the young men that were brought up with him, that stood before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he said unto them, What advice give ye that we may return answer
        to this people, which have spoken to me, saying, Ease somewhat the yoke that
        thy father did put upon us? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the young men that were brought up with him spake unto him, saying,
        Thus shalt thou answer the people that spake unto thee, saying, Thy father
        made our yoke heavy, but make thou <i>it</i> somewhat lighter for us; thus
        shalt thou say unto them, My little <i>finger</i> shall be thicker than my
        father''s loins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For whereas my father put a heavy yoke upon you, I will put more
        to your yoke: my father chastised you with whips, but I <i>will chastise
        you</i> with scorpions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam on the third day,
        as the king bade, saying, Come again to me on the third day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the king answered them roughly; and king Rehoboam forsook the
        counsel of the old men, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and answered them after the advice of the young men, saying, My father
        made your yoke heavy, but I will add thereto: my father chastised you with
        whips, but I <i>will chastise you</i> with scorpions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Revolt of Ten Tribes'
      title: Revolt of Ten Tribes
      number: 15
      content: 'So the king hearkened not unto the people: for the cause was of God,
        that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> might perform his word, which he spake
        by the hand of Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And when all Israel <i>saw</i> that the king would not hearken unto
        them, the people answered the king, saying, What portion have we in David?
        and <i>we have</i> none inheritance in the son of Jesse: every man to your
        tents, O Israel: <i>and</i> now, David, see to thine own house. So all Israel
        went to their tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But <i>as for</i> the children of Israel that dwelt in the cities
        of Judah, Rehoboam reigned over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then king Rehoboam sent Hadoram that <i>was</i> over the tribute;
        and the children of Israel stoned him with stones, that he died. But king
        Rehoboam made speed to get him up to <i>his</i> chariot, to flee to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And Israel rebelled against the house of David unto this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem the capital of JudahIts Fortifications and Fenced Cities'
      title: Jerusalem the capital of JudahIts Fortifications and Fenced Cities
      number: 1
      content: '  And when Rehoboam was come to Jerusalem, he gathered of the house
        of Judah and Benjamin an hundred and fourscore thousand chosen <i>men</i>,
        which were warriors, to fight against Israel, that he might bring the kingdom
        again to Rehoboam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came to Shemaiah
        the man of God, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Speak unto Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all
        Israel in Judah and Benjamin, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Ye shall not go up, nor
        fight against your brethren: return every man to his house: for this thing
        is done of me. And they obeyed the words of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and returned from going against Jeroboam.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Rehoboam dwelt in Jerusalem, and built cities for defence in
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He built even Beth-lehem, and Etam, and Tekoa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and Beth-zur, and Shoco, and Adullam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and Gath, and Mareshah, and Ziph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and Adoraim, and Lachish, and Azekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and Zorah, and Aijalon, and Hebron, which <i>are</i> in Judah and
        in Benjamin fenced cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he fortified the strong holds, and put captains in them, and
        store of victual, and of oil and wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And in every several city <i>he put</i> shields and spears, and made
        them exceeding strong, having Judah and Benjamin on his side.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the priests and the Levites that <i>were</i> in all Israel resorted
        to him out of all their coasts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For the Levites left their suburbs and their possession, and came
        to Judah and Jerusalem: for Jeroboam and his sons had cast them off from
        executing the priest''s office unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and he ordained him priests for the high places, and for the devils,
        and for the calves which he had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And after them out of all the tribes of Israel such as set their
        hearts to seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel came to Jerusalem,
        to sacrifice unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So they strengthened the kingdom of Judah, and made Rehoboam the
        son of Solomon strong, three years: for three years they walked in the way
        of David and Solomon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Rehoboam took him Mahalath the daughter of Jerimoth the son of
        David to wife, <i>and</i> Abihail the daughter of Eliab the son of Jesse; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'which bare him children; Jeush, and Shemariah, and Zaham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And after her he took Maachah the daughter of Absalom; which bare
        him Abijah, and Attai, and Ziza, and Shelomith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Rehoboam loved Maachah the daughter of Absalom above all his
        wives and his concubines: (for he took eighteen wives, and threescore concubines;
        and begat twenty and eight sons, and threescore daughters.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Rehoboam made Abijah the son of Maachah the chief, <i>to be</i>
        ruler among his brethren: for <i>he thought</i> to make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he dealt wisely, and dispersed of all his children throughout
        all the countries of Judah and Benjamin, unto every fenced city: and he gave
        them victual in abundance. And he desired many wives.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Attacked by Egypt'
      title: Attacked by Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  And it came to pass, when Rehoboam had established the kingdom,
        and had strengthened himself, he forsook the law of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and all Israel with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it came to pass, <i>that</i> in the fifth year of king Rehoboam
        Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem, because they had transgressed
        against the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'with twelve hundred chariots, and threescore thousand horsemen: and
        the people <i>were</i> without number that came with him out of Egypt; the
        Lubims, the Sukkiims, and the Ethiopians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he took the fenced cities which <i>pertained</i> to Judah, and
        came to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then came Shemaiah the prophet to Rehoboam, and <i>to</i> the princes
        of Judah, that were gathered together to Jerusalem because of Shishak, and
        said unto them, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Ye have forsaken
        me, and therefore have I also left you in the hand of Shishak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Whereupon the princes of Israel and the king humbled themselves;
        and they said, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> righteous. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> saw that they humbled themselves,
        the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came to Shemaiah, saying, They
        have humbled themselves; <i>therefore</i> I will not destroy them, but I
        will grant them some deliverance; and my wrath shall not be poured out upon
        Jerusalem by the hand of Shishak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Nevertheless they shall be his servants; that they may know my service,
        and the service of the kingdoms of the countries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem, and took away
        the treasures of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and the treasures
        of the king''s house; he took all: he carried away also the shields of gold
        which Solomon had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Instead of which king Rehoboam made shields of brass, and committed
        <i>them</i> to the hands of the chief of the guard, that kept the entrance
        of the king''s house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And when the king entered into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        the guard came and fetched them, and brought them again into the guard chamber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when he humbled himself, the wrath of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        turned from him, that he would not destroy <i>him</i> altogether: and also
        in Judah things went well.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So king Rehoboam strengthened himself in Jerusalem, and reigned:
        for Rehoboam <i>was</i> one and forty years old when he began to reign, and
        he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city which the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        had chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, to put his name there. And his
        mother''s name <i>was</i> Naamah an Ammonitess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he did evil, because he prepared not his heart to seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the acts of Rehoboam, first and last, <i>are</i> they not written
        in the book of Shemaiah the prophet, and of Iddo the seer concerning genealogies?
        And <i>there were</i> wars between Rehoboam and Jeroboam continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Rehoboam slept with his fathers, and was buried in the city of
        David: and Abijah his son reigned in his stead.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abijah''s Reign'
      title: Abijah's Reign
      number: 1
      content: '  Now in the eighteenth year of king Jeroboam began Abijah to reign
        over Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He reigned three years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name also <i>was</i>
        Michaiah the daughter of Uriel of Gibeah. And there was war between Abijah
        and Jeroboam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Abijah set the battle in array with an army of valiant men of
        war, <i>even</i> four hundred thousand chosen men: Jeroboam also set the
        battle in array against him with eight hundred thousand chosen men, <i>being</i>
        mighty men of valour.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Abijah stood up upon mount Zemaraim, which <i>is</i> in mount
        Ephraim, and said, Hear me, thou Jeroboam, and all Israel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'ought ye not to know that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of
        Israel gave the kingdom over Israel to David for ever, <i>even</i> to him
        and to his sons by a covenant of salt? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Yet Jeroboam the son of Nebat, the servant of Solomon the son of
        David, is risen up, and hath rebelled against his lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And there are gathered unto him vain men, the children of Belial,
        and have strengthened themselves against Rehoboam the son of Solomon, when
        Rehoboam was young and tenderhearted, and could not withstand them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And now ye think to withstand the kingdom of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        in the hand of the sons of David; and ye <i>be</i> a great multitude, and
        <i>there are</i> with you golden calves, which Jeroboam made you for gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have ye not cast out the priests of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        the sons of Aaron, and the Levites, and have made you priests after the manner
        of the nations of <i>other</i> lands? so that whosoever cometh to consecrate
        himself with a young bullock and seven rams, <i>the same</i> may be a priest
        of <i>them that are</i> no gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But as for us, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> our God,
        and we have not forsaken him; and the priests, which minister unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        <i>are</i> the sons of Aaron, and the Levites <i>wait</i> upon <i>their</i>
        business: '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and they burn unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> every morning
        and every evening burnt sacrifices and sweet incense: the shewbread also
        <i>set they in order</i> upon the pure table; and the candlestick of gold
        with the lamps thereof, to burn every evening: for we keep the charge of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> our God; but ye have forsaken him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And, behold, God himself <i>is</i> with us for <i>our</i> captain,
        and his priests with sounding trumpets to cry alarm against you. O children
        of Israel, fight ye not against the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of your
        fathers; for ye shall not prosper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But Jeroboam caused an ambushment to come about behind them: so they
        were before Judah, and the ambushment <i>was</i> behind them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when Judah looked back, behold, the battle <i>was</i> before
        and behind: and they cried unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and the
        priests sounded with the trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the men of Judah gave a shout: and as the men of Judah shouted,
        it came to pass, that God smote Jeroboam and all Israel before Abijah and
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the children of Israel fled before Judah: and God delivered them
        into their hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Abijah and his people slew them with a great slaughter: so there
        fell down slain of Israel five hundred thousand chosen men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Thus the children of Israel were brought under at that time, and
        the children of Judah prevailed, because they relied upon the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Abijah pursued after Jeroboam, and took cities from him, Beth-el
        with the towns thereof, and Jeshanah with the towns thereof, and Ephrain
        with the towns thereof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Neither did Jeroboam recover strength again in the days of Abijah:
        and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> struck him, and he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But Abijah waxed mighty, and married fourteen wives, and begat twenty
        and two sons, and sixteen daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And the rest of the acts of Abijah, and his ways, and his sayings,
        <i>are</i> written in the story of the prophet Iddo.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Asa'
      title: Asa
      number: 1
      content: '  So Abijah slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city
        of David: and Asa his son reigned in his stead. In his days the land was
        quiet ten years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Asa did <i>that which was</i> good and right in the eyes of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'for he took away the altars of the strange <i>gods</i>, and the high
        places, and brake down the images, and cut down the groves: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and commanded Judah to seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of
        their fathers, and to do the law and the commandment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Also he took away out of all the cities of Judah the high places
        and the images: and the kingdom was quiet before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he built fenced cities in Judah: for the land had rest, and he
        had no war in those years; because the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had given
        him rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore he said unto Judah, Let us build these cities, and make
        about <i>them</i> walls, and towers, gates, and bars, <i>while</i> the land
        <i>is</i> yet before us; because we have sought the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        our God, we have sought <i>him</i>, and he hath given us rest on every side.
        So they built and prospered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Asa had an army <i>of men</i> that bare targets and spears, out
        of Judah three hundred thousand; and out of Benjamin, that bare shields and
        drew bows, two hundred and fourscore thousand: all these <i>were</i> mighty
        men of valour.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And there came out against them Zerah the Ethiopian with an host
        of a thousand thousand, and three hundred chariots; and came unto Mareshah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Asa went out against him, and they set the battle in array in
        the valley of Zephathah at Mareshah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Asa cried unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God, and said,
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, <i>it is</i> nothing with thee to help, whether
        with many, or with them that have no power: help us, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        our God; for we rest on thee, and in thy name we go against this multitude.
        O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, thou <i>art</i> our God; let not man prevail
        against thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> smote the Ethiopians before Asa,
        and before Judah; and the Ethiopians fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Asa and the people that <i>were</i> with him pursued them unto
        Gerar: and the Ethiopians were overthrown, that they could not recover themselves;
        for they were destroyed before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and before
        his host; and they carried away very much spoil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they smote all the cities round about Gerar; for the fear of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came upon them: and they spoiled all the
        cities; for there was exceeding much spoil in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: They smote also the tents of cattle, and carried away sheep and camels
        in abundance, and returned to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Prophecy of Oded'
      title: The Prophecy of Oded
      number: 1
      content: '  And the Spirit of God came upon Azariah the son of Oded: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and he went out to meet Asa, and said unto him, Hear ye me, Asa,
        and all Judah and Benjamin; The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> with
        you, while ye be with him; and if ye seek him, he will be found of you; but
        if ye forsake him, he will forsake you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now for a long season Israel <i>hath been</i> without the true God,
        and without a teaching priest, and without law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But when they in their trouble did turn unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel, and sought him, he was found of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And in those times <i>there was</i> no peace to him that went out,
        nor to him that came in, but great vexations <i>were</i> upon all the inhabitants
        of the countries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And nation was destroyed of nation, and city of city: for God did
        vex them with all adversity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Be ye strong therefore, and let not your hands be weak: for your
        work shall be rewarded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when Asa heard these words, and the prophecy of Oded the prophet,
        he took courage, and put away the abominable idols out of all the land of
        Judah and Benjamin, and out of the cities which he had taken from mount Ephraim,
        and renewed the altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, that <i>was</i>
        before the porch of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he gathered all Judah and Benjamin, and the strangers with them
        out of Ephraim and Manasseh, and out of Simeon: for they fell to him out
        of Israel in abundance, when they saw that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        his God <i>was</i> with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So they gathered themselves together at Jerusalem in the third month,
        in the fifteenth year of the reign of Asa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they offered unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> the same time,
        of the spoil <i>which</i> they had brought, seven hundred oxen and seven
        thousand sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they entered into a covenant to seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of their fathers with all their heart and with all their soul; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'that whosoever would not seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God
        of Israel should be put to death, whether small or great, whether man or
        woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they sware unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> with a loud voice,
        and with shouting, and with trumpets, and with cornets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And all Judah rejoiced at the oath: for they had sworn with all their
        heart, and sought him with their whole desire; and he was found of them:
        and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> gave them rest round about.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And also <i>concerning</i> Maachah the mother of Asa the king, he
        removed her from <i>being</i> queen, because she had made an idol in a grove:
        and Asa cut down her idol, and stamped <i>it</i>, and burnt <i>it</i> at
        the brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But the high places were not taken away out of Israel: nevertheless
        the heart of Asa was perfect all his days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he brought into the house of God the things that his father had
        dedicated, and that he himself had dedicated, silver, and gold, and vessels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And there was no <i>more</i> war unto the five and thirtieth year
        of the reign of Asa.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  In the six and thirtieth year of the reign of Asa Baasha king of
        Israel came up against Judah, and built Ramah, to the intent that he might
        let none go out or come in to Asa king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Asa brought out silver and gold out of the treasures of the
        house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> and of the king''s house, and sent
        to Ben-hadad king of Syria, that dwelt at Damascus, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<i>There is</i> a league between me and thee, as <i>there was</i>
        between my father and thy father: behold, I have sent thee silver and gold;
        go, break thy league with Baasha king of Israel, that he may depart from
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Ben-hadad hearkened unto king Asa, and sent the captains of his
        armies against the cities of Israel; and they smote Ijon, and Dan, and Abel-maim,
        and all the store cities of Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Baasha heard <i>it</i>, that he left off
        building of Ramah, and let his work cease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Asa the king took all Judah; and they carried away the stones
        of Ramah, and the timber thereof, wherewith Baasha was building; and he built
        therewith Geba and Mizpah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And at that time Hanani the seer came to Asa king of Judah, and said
        unto him, Because thou hast relied on the king of Syria, and not relied on
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God, therefore is the host of the king
        of Syria escaped out of thine hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Were not the Ethiopians and the Lubims a huge host, with very many
        chariots and horsemen? yet, because thou didst rely on the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        he delivered them into thine hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For the eyes of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> run to and fro throughout
        the whole earth, to shew himself strong in the behalf of <i>them</i> whose
        heart <i>is</i> perfect toward him. Herein thou hast done foolishly: therefore
        from henceforth thou shalt have wars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Asa was wroth with the seer, and put him in a prison house;
        for <i>he was</i> in a rage with him because of this <i>thing</i>. And Asa
        oppressed <i>some</i> of the people the same time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And, behold, the acts of Asa, first and last, lo, they <i>are</i>
        written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Asa in the thirty and ninth year of his reign was diseased in
        his feet, until his disease <i>was</i> exceeding <i>great:</i> yet in his
        disease he sought not to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, but to the physicians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Asa slept with his fathers, and died in the one and fortieth
        year of his reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they buried him in his own sepulchres, which he had made for
        himself in the city of David, and laid him in the bed which was filled with
        sweet odours and divers kinds <i>of spices</i> prepared by the apothecaries''
        art: and they made a very great burning for him.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoshaphat'
      title: Jehoshaphat
      number: 1
      content: '  And Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his stead, and strengthened
        himself against Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he placed forces in all the fenced cities of Judah, and set garrisons
        in the land of Judah, and in the cities of Ephraim, which Asa his father
        had taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> was with Jehoshaphat, because
        he walked in the first ways of his father David, and sought not unto Baalim; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but sought to the <i><span class="ChapterContent_content__RrUqA">LORD</span></i>LORD
        God of his father, and walked in his commandments, and not after the doings
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> stablished the kingdom
        in his hand; and all Judah brought to Jehoshaphat presents; and he had riches
        and honour in abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And his heart was lifted up in the ways of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        moreover he took away the high places and groves out of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Also in the third year of his reign he sent to his princes, <i>even</i>
        to Ben-hail, and to Obadiah, and to Zechariah, and to Nethaneel, and to Michaiah,
        to teach in the cities of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And with them <i>he sent</i> Levites, <i>even</i> Shemaiah, and Nethaniah,
        and Zebadiah, and Asahel, and Shemiramoth, and Jehonathan, and Adonijah,
        and Tobijah, and Tob-adonijah, Levites; and with them Elishama and Jehoram,
        priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they taught in Judah, and <i>had</i> the book of the law of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> with them, and went about throughout all the
        cities of Judah, and taught the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the fear of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> fell upon all the
        kingdoms of the lands that <i>were</i> round about Judah, so that they made
        no war against Jehoshaphat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Also <i>some</i> of the Philistines brought Jehoshaphat presents,
        and tribute silver; and the Arabians brought him flocks, seven thousand and
        seven hundred rams, and seven thousand and seven hundred he goats.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat waxed great exceedingly; and he built in Judah castles,
        and cities of store. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he had much business in the cities of Judah: and the men of war,
        mighty men of valour, <i>were</i> in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And these <i>are</i> the numbers of them according to the house of
        their fathers: Of Judah, the captains of thousands; Adnah the chief, and
        with him mighty men of valour three hundred thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And next to him <i>was</i> Jehohanan the captain, and with him two
        hundred and fourscore thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And next him <i>was</i> Amasiah the son of Zichri, who willingly
        offered himself unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; and with him two hundred
        thousand mighty men of valour. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And of Benjamin; Eliada a mighty man of valour, and with him armed
        men with bow and shield two hundred thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And next him <i>was</i> Jehozabad, and with him an hundred and fourscore
        thousand ready prepared for the war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: These waited on the king, beside <i>those</i> whom the king put in
        the fenced cities throughout all Judah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Jehoshaphat had riches and honour in abundance, and joined
        affinity with Ahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And after <i>certain</i> years he went down to Ahab to Samaria. And
        Ahab killed sheep and oxen for him in abundance, and for the people that
        <i>he had</i> with him, and persuaded him to go up <i>with him</i> to Ramoth-gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Prophecy of Micaiah'
      title: The Prophecy of Micaiah
      number: 3
      content: 'And Ahab king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat king of Judah, Wilt
        thou go with me to Ramoth-gilead? And he answered him, I <i>am</i> as thou
        <i>art</i>, and my people as thy people; and <i>we will be</i> with thee
        in the war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat said unto the king of Israel, Enquire, I pray thee,
        at the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> to day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore the king of Israel gathered together of prophets four hundred
        men, and said unto them, Shall we go to Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall
        I forbear? And they said, Go up; for God will deliver <i>it</i> into the
        king''s hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But Jehoshaphat said, <i>Is there</i> not here a prophet of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        besides, that we might enquire of him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat, <i>There is</i> yet
        one man, by whom we may enquire of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: but I
        hate him; for he never prophesied good unto me, but always evil: the same
        <i>is</i> Micaiah the son of Imla. And Jehoshaphat said, Let not the king
        say so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the king of Israel called for one <i>of his</i> officers, and
        said, Fetch quickly Micaiah the son of Imla. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah sat either of
        them on his throne, clothed in <i>their</i> robes, and they sat in a void
        place at the entering in of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets prophesied
        before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah had made him horns of iron, and
        said, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, With these thou shalt push
        Syria until they be consumed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And all the prophets prophesied so, saying, Go up to Ramoth-gilead,
        and prosper: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall deliver <i>it</i>
        into the hand of the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the messenger that went to call Micaiah spake to him, saying,
        Behold, the words of the prophets <i>declare</i> good to the king with one
        assent; let thy word therefore, I pray thee, be like one of their''s, and
        speak thou good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Micaiah said, <i>As</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> liveth,
        even what my God saith, that will I speak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when he was come to the king, the king said unto him, Micaiah,
        shall we go to Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall I forbear? And he said,
        Go ye up, and prosper, and they shall be delivered into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the king said to him, How many times shall I adjure thee that
        thou say nothing but the truth to me in the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then he said, I did see all Israel scattered upon the mountains,
        as sheep that have no shepherd: and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said,
        These have no master; let them return <i>therefore</i> every man to his house
        in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, Did I not tell thee <i>that</i>
        he would not prophesy good unto me, but evil? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Again he said, Therefore hear the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        I saw the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> sitting upon his throne, and all the
        host of heaven standing on his right hand and <i>on</i> his left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said, Who shall entice Ahab king
        of Israel, that he may go up and fall at Ramoth-gilead? And one spake saying
        after this manner, and another saying after that manner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then there came out a spirit, and stood before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and said, I will entice him. And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto
        him, Wherewith? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And he said, I will go out, and be a lying spirit in the mouth of
        all his prophets. And <i>the </i><smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said, Thou shalt
        entice <i>him</i>, and thou shalt also prevail: go out, and do <i>even</i>
        so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now therefore, behold, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath put a
        lying spirit in the mouth of these thy prophets, and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath spoken evil against thee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came near, and smote Micaiah upon
        the cheek, and said, Which way went the Spirit of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        from me to speak unto thee? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Micaiah said, Behold, thou shalt see on that day when thou shalt
        go into an inner chamber to hide thyself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then the king of Israel said, Take ye Micaiah, and carry him back
        to Amon the governor of the city, and to Joash the king''s son; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and say, Thus saith the king, Put this <i>fellow</i> in the prison,
        and feed him with bread of affliction and with water of affliction, until
        I return in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Micaiah said, If thou certainly return in peace, <i>then</i>
        hath not the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> spoken by me. And he said, Hearken,
        all ye people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to
        Ramoth-gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat, I will disguise myself,
        and will go to the battle; but put thou on thy robes. So the king of Israel
        disguised himself; and they went to the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now the king of Syria had commanded the captains of the chariots
        that <i>were</i> with him, saying, Fight ye not with small or great, save
        only with the king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And it came to pass, when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat,
        that they said, It <i>is</i> the king of Israel. Therefore they compassed
        about him to fight: but Jehoshaphat cried out, and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        helped him; and God moved them <i>to depart</i> from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For it came to pass, that, when the captains of the chariots perceived
        that it was not the king of Israel, they turned back again from pursuing
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And a <i>certain</i> man drew a bow at a venture, and smote the king
        of Israel between the joints of the harness: therefore he said to his chariot
        man, Turn thine hand, that thou mayest carry me out of the host; for I am
        wounded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And the battle increased that day: howbeit the king of Israel stayed
        <i>himself</i> up in <i>his</i> chariot against the Syrians until the even:
        and about the time of the sun going down he died.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  And Jehoshaphat the king of Judah returned to his house in peace
        to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Jehu the son of Hanani the seer went out to meet him, and said
        to king Jehoshaphat, Shouldest thou help the ungodly, and love them that
        hate the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>? therefore <i>is</i> wrath upon thee
        from before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Nevertheless there are good things found in thee, in that thou hast
        taken away the groves out of the land, and hast prepared thine heart to seek
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat dwelt at Jerusalem: and he went out again through
        the people from Beer-sheba to mount Ephraim, and brought them back unto the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he set judges in the land throughout all the fenced cities of
        Judah, city by city, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and said to the judges, Take heed what ye do: for ye judge not for
        man, but for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, who <i>is</i> with you in the
        judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Wherefore now let the fear of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> be
        upon you; take heed and do <i>it:</i> for <i>there is</i> no iniquity with
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> our God, nor respect of persons, nor taking
        of gifts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Moreover in Jerusalem did Jehoshaphat set of the Levites, and <i>of</i>
        the priests, and of the chief of the fathers of Israel, for the judgment
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and for controversies, when they returned
        to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he charged them, saying, Thus shall ye do in the fear of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, faithfully, and with a perfect heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And what cause soever shall come to you of your brethren that dwell
        in their cities, between blood and blood, between law and commandment, statutes
        and judgments, ye shall even warn them that they trespass not against the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and <i>so</i> wrath come upon you, and upon
        your brethren: this do, and ye shall not trespass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And, behold, Amariah the chief priest <i>is</i> over you in all matters
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; and Zebadiah the son of Ishmael, the
        ruler of the house of Judah, for all the king''s matters: also the Levites
        <i>shall be</i> officers before you. Deal courageously, and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        shall be with the good.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  It came to pass after this also, <i>that</i> the children of Moab,
        and the children of Ammon, and with them <i>other</i> beside the Ammonites,
        came against Jehoshaphat to battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then there came some that told Jehoshaphat, saying, There cometh
        a great multitude against thee from beyond the sea on this side Syria; and,
        behold, they <i>be</i> in Hazazon-tamar, which <i>is</i> Engedi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat feared, and set himself to seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and proclaimed a fast throughout all Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Jehoshaphat''s Prayer'
      title: Jehoshaphat's Prayer
      number: 4
      content: 'And Judah gathered themselves together, to ask <i>help</i> of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: even out of all the cities of Judah they came
        to seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat stood in the congregation of Judah and Jerusalem,
        in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, before the new court, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and said, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of our fathers, <i>art</i>
        not thou God in heaven? and rulest <i>not</i> thou over all the kingdoms
        of the heathen? and in thine hand <i>is there not</i> power and might, so
        that none is able to withstand thee? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<i>Art</i> not thou our God, <i>who</i> didst drive out the inhabitants
        of this land before thy people Israel, and gavest it to the seed of Abraham
        thy friend for ever? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And they dwelt therein, and have built thee a sanctuary therein for
        thy name, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If, <i>when</i> evil cometh upon us, <i>as</i> the sword, judgment,
        or pestilence, or famine, we stand before this house, and in thy presence,
        (for thy name <i>is</i> in this house,) and cry unto thee in our affliction,
        then thou wilt hear and help. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now, behold, the children of Ammon and Moab and mount Seir, whom
        thou wouldest not let Israel invade, when they came out of the land of Egypt,
        but they turned from them, and destroyed them not; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'behold, <i>I say, how</i> they reward us, to come to cast us out
        of thy possession, which thou hast given us to inherit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'O our God, wilt thou not judge them? for we have no might against
        this great company that cometh against us; neither know we what to do: but
        our eyes <i>are</i> upon thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And all Judah stood before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, with
        their little ones, their wives, and their children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then upon Jahaziel the son of Zechariah, the son of Benaiah, the
        son of Jeiel, the son of Mattaniah, a Levite of the sons of Asaph, came the
        Spirit of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> in the midst of the congregation; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and he said, Hearken ye, all Judah, and ye inhabitants of Jerusalem,
        and thou king Jehoshaphat, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> unto
        you, Be not afraid nor dismayed by reason of this great multitude; for the
        battle <i>is</i> not your''s, but God''s. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'To morrow go ye down against them: behold, they come up by the cliff
        of Ziz; and ye shall find them at the end of the brook, before the wilderness
        of Jeruel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Ye shall not <i>need</i> to fight in this <i>battle:</i> set yourselves,
        stand ye <i>still</i>, and see the salvation of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        with you, O Judah and Jerusalem: fear not, nor be dismayed; to morrow go
        out against them: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>will be</i> with
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat bowed his head with <i>his</i> face to the ground:
        and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem fell before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        worshipping the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the Levites, of the children of the Kohathites, and of the children
        of the Korhites, stood up to praise the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of
        Israel with a loud voice on high.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And they rose early in the morning, and went forth into the wilderness
        of Tekoa: and as they went forth, Jehoshaphat stood and said, Hear me, O
        Judah, and ye inhabitants of Jerusalem; Believe in the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        your God, so shall ye be established; believe his prophets, so shall ye prosper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when he had consulted with the people, he appointed singers unto
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and that should praise the beauty of holiness,
        as they went out before the army, and to say, Praise the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        for his mercy <i>endureth</i> for ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And when they began to sing and to praise, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        set ambushments against the children of Ammon, Moab, and mount Seir, which
        were come against Judah; and they were smitten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the children of Ammon and Moab stood up against the inhabitants
        of mount Seir, utterly to slay and destroy <i>them:</i> and when they had
        made an end of the inhabitants of Seir, every one helped to destroy another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And when Judah came toward the watch tower in the wilderness, they
        looked unto the multitude, and, behold, they <i>were</i> dead bodies fallen
        to the earth, and none escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And when Jehoshaphat and his people came to take away the spoil of
        them, they found among them in abundance both riches with the dead bodies,
        and precious jewels, which they stripped off for themselves, more than they
        could carry away: and they were three days in gathering of the spoil, it
        was so much. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And on the fourth day they assembled themselves in the valley of
        Berachah; for there they blessed the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: therefore
        the name of the same place was called, The valley of Berachah, unto this
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then they returned, every man of Judah and Jerusalem, and Jehoshaphat
        in the forefront of them, to go again to Jerusalem with joy; for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        had made them to rejoice over their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And they came to Jerusalem with psalteries and harps and trumpets
        unto the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the fear of God was on all the kingdoms of <i>those</i> countries,
        when they had heard that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> fought against the
        enemies of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So the realm of Jehoshaphat was quiet: for his God gave him rest
        round about.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat reigned over Judah: <i>he was</i> thirty and five
        years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty and five years in
        Jerusalem. And his mother''s name <i>was</i> Azubah the daughter of Shilhi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he walked in the way of Asa his father, and departed not from
        it, doing <i>that which was</i> right in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Howbeit the high places were not taken away: for as yet the people
        had not prepared their hearts unto the God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, first and last, behold,
        they <i>are</i> written in the book of Jehu the son of Hanani, who <i>is</i>
        mentioned in the book of the kings of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And after this did Jehoshaphat king of Judah join himself with Ahaziah
        king of Israel, who did very wickedly: '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and he joined himself with him to make ships to go to Tarshish: and
        they made the ships in Ezion-geber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Then Eliezer the son of Dodavah of Mareshah prophesied against Jehoshaphat,
        saying, Because thou hast joined thyself with Ahaziah, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath broken thy works. And the ships were broken, that they were not able
        to go to Tarshish.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoram'
      title: Jehoram
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers, and was buried with his
        fathers in the city of David. And Jehoram his son reigned in his stead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he had brethren the sons of Jehoshaphat, Azariah, and Jehiel,
        and Zechariah, and Azariah, and Michael, and Shephatiah: all these <i>were</i>
        the sons of Jehoshaphat king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And their father gave them great gifts of silver, and of gold, and
        of precious things, with fenced cities in Judah: but the kingdom gave he
        to Jehoram; because he <i>was</i> the firstborn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now when Jehoram was risen up to the kingdom of his father, he strengthened
        himself, and slew all his brethren with the sword, and <i>divers</i> also
        of the princes of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Jehoram <i>was</i> thirty and two years old when he began to reign,
        and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, like as did the
        house of Ahab: for he had the daughter of Ahab to wife: and he wrought <i>that
        which was</i> evil in the eyes of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Howbeit the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> would not destroy the house
        of David, because of the covenant that he had made with David, and as he
        promised to give a light to him and to his sons for ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In his days the Edomites revolted from under the dominion of Judah,
        and made themselves a king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Jehoram went forth with his princes, and all his chariots with
        him: and he rose up by night, and smote the Edomites which compassed him
        in, and the captains of the chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the Edomites revolted from under the hand of Judah unto this day.
        The same time <i>also</i> did Libnah revolt from under his hand; because
        he had forsaken the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of his fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moreover he made high places in the mountains of Judah, and caused
        the inhabitants of Jerusalem to commit fornication, and compelled Judah <i>thereto</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And there came a writing to him from Elijah the prophet, saying,
        Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of David thy father, Because
        thou hast not walked in the ways of Jehoshaphat thy father, nor in the ways
        of Asa king of Judah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'but hast walked in the way of the kings of Israel, and hast made
        Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to go a whoring, like to the whoredoms
        of the house of Ahab, and also hast slain thy brethren of thy father''s house,
        <i>which were</i> better than thyself: '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'behold, with a great plague will the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        smite thy people, and thy children, and thy wives, and all thy goods: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and thou <i>shalt have</i> great sickness by disease of thy bowels,
        until thy bowels fall out by reason of the sickness day by day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> stirred up against Jehoram
        the spirit of the Philistines, and of the Arabians, that <i>were</i> near
        the Ethiopians: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and they came up into Judah, and brake into it, and carried away
        all the substance that was found in the king''s house, and his sons also,
        and his wives; so that there was never a son left him, save Jehoahaz, the
        youngest of his sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And after all this the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> smote him in his
        bowels with an incurable disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And it came to pass, that in process of time, after the end of two
        years, his bowels fell out by reason of his sickness: so he died of sore
        diseases. And his people made no burning for him, like the burning of his
        fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Thirty and two years old was he when he began to reign, and he reigned
        in Jerusalem eight years, and departed without being desired. Howbeit they
        buried him in the city of David, but not in the sepulchres of the kings.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaziah'
      title: Ahaziah
      number: 1
      content: '  And the inhabitants of Jerusalem made Ahaziah his youngest son
        king in his stead: for the band of men that came with the Arabians to the
        camp had slain all the eldest. So Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah
        reigned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Forty and two years old <i>was</i> Ahaziah when he began to reign,
        and he reigned one year in Jerusalem. His mother''s name also <i>was</i>
        Athaliah the daughter of Omri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He also walked in the ways of the house of Ahab: for his mother was
        his counsellor to do wickedly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Wherefore he did evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        like the house of Ahab: for they were his counsellors after the death of
        his father to his destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He walked also after their counsel, and went with Jehoram the son
        of Ahab king of Israel to war against Hazael king of Syria at Ramoth-gilead:
        and the Syrians smote Joram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he returned to be healed in Jezreel because of the wounds which
        were given him at Ramah, when he fought with Hazael king of Syria. And Azariah
        the son of Jehoram king of Judah went down to see Jehoram the son of Ahab
        at Jezreel, because he was sick.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the destruction of Ahaziah was of God by coming to Joram: for
        when he was come, he went out with Jehoram against Jehu the son of Nimshi,
        whom the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had anointed to cut off the house of
        Ahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it came to pass, that, when Jehu was executing judgment upon
        the house of Ahab, and found the princes of Judah, and the sons of the brethren
        of Ahaziah, that ministered to Ahaziah, he slew them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Athaliah'
      title: Athaliah
      number: 9
      content: 'And he sought Ahaziah: and they caught him, (for he was hid in Samaria,)
        and brought him to Jehu: and when they had slain him, they buried him: Because,
        said they, he <i>is</i> the son of Jehoshaphat, who sought the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        with all his heart. So the house of Ahaziah had no power to keep still the
        kingdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead,
        she arose and destroyed all the seed royal of the house of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Jehoshabeath, the daughter of the king, took Joash the son of
        Ahaziah, and stole him from among the king''s sons that were slain, and put
        him and his nurse in a bedchamber. So Jehoshabeath, the daughter of king
        Jehoram, the wife of Jehoiada the priest, (for she was the sister of Ahaziah,)
        hid him from Athaliah, so that she slew him not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he was with them hid in the house of God six years: and Athaliah
        reigned over the land.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  And in the seventh year Jehoiada strengthened himself, and took
        the captains of hundreds, Azariah the son of Jeroham, and Ishmael the son
        of Jehohanan, and Azariah the son of Obed, and Maaseiah the son of Adaiah,
        and Elishaphat the son of Zichri, into covenant with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And they went about in Judah, and gathered the Levites out of all
        the cities of Judah, and the chief of the fathers of Israel, and they came
        to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And all the congregation made a covenant with the king in the house
        of God. And he said unto them, Behold, the king''s son shall reign, as the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath said of the sons of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This <i>is</i> the thing that ye shall do; A third part of you entering
        on the sabbath, of the priests and of the Levites, <i>shall be</i> porters
        of the doors; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and a third part <i>shall be</i> at the king''s house; and a third
        part at the gate of the foundation: and all the people <i>shall be</i> in
        the courts of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But let none come into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        save the priests, and they that minister of the Levites; they shall go in,
        for they <i>are</i> holy: but all the people shall keep the watch of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the Levites shall compass the king round about, every man with
        his weapons in his hand; and whosoever <i>else</i> cometh into the house,
        he shall be put to death: but be ye with the king when he cometh in, and
        when he goeth out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the Levites and all Judah did according to all things that Jehoiada
        the priest had commanded, and took every man his men that were to come in
        on the sabbath, with them that were to go <i>out</i> on the sabbath: for
        Jehoiada the priest dismissed not the courses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Moreover Jehoiada the priest delivered to the captains of hundreds
        spears, and bucklers, and shields, that <i>had been</i> king David''s, which
        <i>were</i> in the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he set all the people, every man having his weapon in his hand,
        from the right side of the temple to the left side of the temple, along by
        the altar and the temple, by the king round about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then they brought out the king''s son, and put upon him the crown,
        and <i>gave him</i> the testimony, and made him king. And Jehoiada and his
        sons anointed him, and said, God save the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now when Athaliah heard the noise of the people running and praising
        the king, she came to the people into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and she looked, and, behold, the king stood at his pillar at the
        entering in, and the princes and the trumpets by the king: and all the people
        of the land rejoiced, and sounded with trumpets, also the singers with instruments
        of musick, and such as taught to sing praise. Then Athaliah rent her clothes,
        and said, Treason, Treason. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Jehoiada the priest brought out the captains of hundreds that
        were set over the host, and said unto them, Have her forth of the ranges:
        and whoso followeth her, let him be slain with the sword. For the priest
        said, Slay her not in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So they laid hands on her; and when she was come to the entering
        of the horse gate by the king''s house, they slew her there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Jehoiada made a covenant between him, and between all the people,
        and between the king, that they should be the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>''s
        people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then all the people went to the house of Baal, and brake it down,
        and brake his altars and his images in pieces, and slew Mattan the priest
        of Baal before the altars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Also Jehoiada appointed the offices of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        by the hand of the priests the Levites, whom David had distributed in the
        house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, to offer the burnt offerings of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, as <i>it is</i> written in the law of Moses,
        with rejoicing and with singing, <i>as it was ordained</i> by David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he set the porters at the gates of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        that none <i>which was</i> unclean in any thing should enter in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And he took the captains of hundreds, and the nobles, and the governors
        of the people, and all the people of the land, and brought down the king
        from the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: and they came through
        the high gate into the king''s house, and set the king upon the throne of
        the kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And all the people of the land rejoiced: and the city was quiet,
        after that they had slain Athaliah with the sword.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joash'
      title: Joash
      number: 1
      content: '  Joash <i>was</i> seven years old when he began to reign, and he
        reigned forty years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name also <i>was</i> Zibiah
        of Beer-sheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Joash did <i>that which was</i> right in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        all the days of Jehoiada the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Jehoiada took for him two wives; and he begat sons and daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And it came to pass after this, <i>that</i> Joash was minded to repair
        the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he gathered together the priests and the Levites, and said to
        them, Go out unto the cities of Judah, and gather of all Israel money to
        repair the house of your God from year to year, and see that ye hasten the
        matter. Howbeit the Levites hastened <i>it</i> not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the king called for Jehoiada the chief, and said unto him, Why
        hast thou not required of the Levites to bring in out of Judah and out of
        Jerusalem the collection, <i>according to the commandment</i> of Moses the
        servant of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and of the congregation of Israel,
        for the tabernacle of witness? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the sons of Athaliah, that wicked woman, had broken up the house
        of God; and also all the dedicated things of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        did they bestow upon Baalim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And at the king''s commandment they made a chest, and set it without
        at the gate of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they made a proclamation through Judah and Jerusalem, to bring
        in to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> the collection <i>that</i> Moses the
        servant of God <i>laid</i> upon Israel in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And all the princes and all the people rejoiced, and brought in,
        and cast into the chest, until they had made an end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now it came to pass, that at what time the chest was brought unto
        the king''s office by the hand of the Levites, and when they saw that <i>there
        was</i> much money, the king''s scribe and the high priest''s officer came
        and emptied the chest, and took it, and carried it to his place again. Thus
        they did day by day, and gathered money in abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the king and Jehoiada gave it to such as did the work of the
        service of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and hired masons
        and carpenters to repair the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and
        also such as wrought iron and brass to mend the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the workmen wrought, and the work was perfected by them, and they
        set the house of God in his state, and strengthened it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when they had finished <i>it</i>, they brought the rest of the
        money before the king and Jehoiada, whereof were made vessels for the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, <i>even</i> vessels to minister, and
        to offer <i>withal</i>, and spoons, and vessels of gold and silver. And they
        offered burnt offerings in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> continually
        all the days of Jehoiada.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But Jehoiada waxed old, and was full of days when he died; an hundred
        and thirty years old <i>was he</i> when he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And they buried him in the city of David among the kings, because
        he had done good in Israel, both toward God, and toward his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now after the death of Jehoiada came the princes of Judah, and made
        obeisance to the king. Then the king hearkened unto them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And they left the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of
        their fathers, and served groves and idols: and wrath came upon Judah and
        Jerusalem for this their trespass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Yet he sent prophets to them, to bring them again unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        and they testified against them: but they would not give ear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the Spirit of God came upon Zechariah the son of Jehoiada the
        priest, which stood above the people, and said unto them, Thus saith God,
        Why transgress ye the commandments of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, that
        ye cannot prosper? because ye have forsaken the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        he hath also forsaken you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they conspired against him, and stoned him with stones at the
        commandment of the king in the court of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Thus Joash the king remembered not the kindness which Jehoiada his
        father had done to him, but slew his son. And when he died, he said, The
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> look upon <i>it</i>, and require <i>it</i>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And it came to pass at the end of the year, <i>that</i> the host
        of Syria came up against him: and they came to Judah and Jerusalem, and destroyed
        all the princes of the people from among the people, and sent all the spoil
        of them unto the king of Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For the army of the Syrians came with a small company of men, and
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> delivered a very great host into their hand,
        because they had forsaken the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of their fathers.
        So they executed judgment against Joash.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And when they were departed from him, (for they left him in great
        diseases,) his own servants conspired against him for the blood of the sons
        of Jehoiada the priest, and slew him on his bed, and he died: and they buried
        him in the city of David, but they buried him not in the sepulchres of the
        kings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And these are they that conspired against him; Zabad the son of Shimeath
        an Ammonitess, and Jehozabad the son of Shimrith a Moabitess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Now <i>concerning</i> his sons, and the greatness of the burdens <i>laid</i>
        upon him, and the repairing of the house of God, behold, they <i>are</i>
        written in the story of the book of the kings. And Amaziah his son reigned
        in his stead.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amaziah'
      title: Amaziah
      number: 1
      content: '  Amaziah <i>was</i> twenty and five years old <i>when</i> he began
        to reign, and he reigned twenty and nine years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s
        name <i>was</i> Jehoaddan of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did <i>that which was</i> right in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        but not with a perfect heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now it came to pass, when the kingdom was established to him, that
        he slew his servants that had killed the king his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But he slew not their children, but <i>did</i> as <i>it is</i> written
        in the law in the book of Moses, where the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> commanded,
        saying, The fathers shall not die for the children, neither shall the children
        die for the fathers, but every man shall die for his own sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Moreover Amaziah gathered Judah together, and made them captains
        over thousands, and captains over hundreds, according to the houses of <i>their</i>
        fathers, throughout all Judah and Benjamin: and he numbered them from twenty
        years old and above, and found them three hundred thousand choice <i>men,
        able</i> to go forth to war, that could handle spear and shield. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He hired also an hundred thousand mighty men of valour out of Israel
        for an hundred talents of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But there came a man of God to him, saying, O king, let not the army
        of Israel go with thee; for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> not
        with Israel, <i>to wit, with</i> all the children of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But if thou wilt go, do <i>it</i>, be strong for the battle: God
        shall make thee fall before the enemy: for God hath power to help, and to
        cast down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Amaziah said to the man of God, But what shall we do for the
        hundred talents which I have given to the army of Israel? And the man of
        God answered, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> is able to give thee much more
        than this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Amaziah separated them, <i>to wit</i>, the army that was come
        to him out of Ephraim, to go home again: wherefore their anger was greatly
        kindled against Judah, and they returned home in great anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Amaziah strengthened himself, and led forth his people, and went
        to the valley of salt, and smote of the children of Seir ten thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And <i>other</i> ten thousand <i>left</i> alive did the children
        of Judah carry away captive, and brought them unto the top of the rock, and
        cast them down from the top of the rock, that they all were broken in pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the soldiers of the army which Amaziah sent back, that they should
        not go with him to battle, fell upon the cities of Judah, from Samaria even
        unto Beth-horon, and smote three thousand of them, and took much spoil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now it came to pass, after that Amaziah was come from the slaughter
        of the Edomites, that he brought the gods of the children of Seir, and set
        them up <i>to be</i> his gods, and bowed down himself before them, and burned
        incense unto them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Wherefore the anger of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> was kindled
        against Amaziah, and he sent unto him a prophet, which said unto him, Why
        hast thou sought after the gods of the people, which could not deliver their
        own people out of thine hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And it came to pass, as he talked with him, that <i>the king</i>
        said unto him, Art thou made of the king''s counsel? forbear; why shouldest
        thou be smitten? Then the prophet forbare, and said, I know that God hath
        determined to destroy thee, because thou hast done this, and hast not hearkened
        unto my counsel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Amaziah king of Judah took advice, and sent to Joash, the son
        of Jehoahaz, the son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, Come, let us see one
        another in the face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Joash king of Israel sent to Amaziah king of Judah, saying, The
        thistle that <i>was</i> in Lebanon sent to the cedar that <i>was</i> in Lebanon,
        saying, Give thy daughter to my son to wife: and there passed by a wild beast
        that <i>was</i> in Lebanon, and trode down the thistle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Thou sayest, Lo, thou hast smitten the Edomites; and thine heart
        lifteth thee up to boast: abide now at home; why shouldest thou meddle to
        <i>thine</i> hurt, that thou shouldest fall, <i>even</i> thou, and Judah
        with thee?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But Amaziah would not hear; for it <i>came</i> of God, that he might
        deliver them into the hand <i>of their enemies</i>, because they sought after
        the gods of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So Joash the king of Israel went up; and they saw one another in
        the face, <i>both</i> he and Amaziah king of Judah, at Beth-shemesh, which
        <i>belongeth</i> to Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Judah was put to the worse before Israel, and they fled every
        man to his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Joash the king of Israel took Amaziah king of Judah, the son
        of Joash, the son of Jehoahaz, at Beth-shemesh, and brought him to Jerusalem,
        and brake down the wall of Jerusalem from the gate of Ephraim to the corner
        gate, four hundred cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And <i>he took</i> all the gold and the silver, and all the vessels
        that were found in the house of God with Obed-edom, and the treasures of
        the king''s house, the hostages also, and returned to Samaria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah lived after the death
        of Joash son of Jehoahaz king of Israel fifteen years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, first and last, behold, <i>are</i>
        they not written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now after the time that Amaziah did turn away from following the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> they made a conspiracy against him in Jerusalem;
        and he fled to Lachish: but they sent to Lachish after him, and slew him
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And they brought him upon horses, and buried him with his fathers
        in the city of Judah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Uzziah'
      title: Uzziah
      number: 1
      content: '  Then all the people of Judah took Uzziah, who <i>was</i> sixteen
        years old, and made him king in the room of his father Amaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He built Eloth, and restored it to Judah, after that the king slept
        with his fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Sixteen years old <i>was</i> Uzziah when he began to reign, and he
        reigned fifty and two years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name also <i>was</i>
        Jecoliah of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he did <i>that which was</i> right in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        according to all that his father Amaziah did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he sought God in the days of Zechariah, who had understanding
        in the visions of God: and as long as he sought the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        God made him to prosper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he went forth and warred against the Philistines, and brake down
        the wall of Gath, and the wall of Jabneh, and the wall of Ashdod, and built
        cities about Ashdod, and among the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And God helped him against the Philistines, and against the Arabians
        that dwelt in Gur-baal, and the Mehunims. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Ammonites gave gifts to Uzziah: and his name spread abroad
        <i>even</i> to the entering in of Egypt; for he strengthened <i>himself</i>
        exceedingly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Moreover Uzziah built towers in Jerusalem at the corner gate, and
        at the valley gate, and at the turning <i>of the wall</i>, and fortified
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Also he built towers in the desert, and digged many wells: for he
        had much cattle, both in the low country, and in the plains: husbandmen <i>also</i>,
        and vine dressers in the mountains, and in Carmel: for he loved husbandry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moreover Uzziah had an host of fighting men, that went out to war
        by bands, according to the number of their account by the hand of Jeiel the
        scribe and Maaseiah the ruler, under the hand of Hananiah, <i>one</i> of
        the king''s captains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The whole number of the chief of the fathers of the mighty men of
        valour <i>were</i> two thousand and six hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And under their hand <i>was</i> an army, three hundred thousand and
        seven thousand and five hundred, that made war with mighty power, to help
        the king against the enemy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Uzziah prepared for them throughout all the host shields, and
        spears, and helmets, and habergeons, and bows, and slings <i>to cast</i>
        stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he made in Jerusalem engines, invented by cunning men, to be
        on the towers and upon the bulwarks, to shoot arrows and great stones withal.
        And his name spread far abroad; for he was marvellously helped, till he was
        strong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But when he was strong, his heart was lifted up to <i>his</i> destruction:
        for he transgressed against the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God, and
        went into the temple of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> to burn incense upon
        the altar of incense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Azariah the priest went in after him, and with him fourscore
        priests of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, <i>that were</i> valiant men: '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and they withstood Uzziah the king, and said unto him, <i>It appertaineth</i>
        not unto thee, Uzziah, to burn incense unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        but to the priests the sons of Aaron, that are consecrated to burn incense:
        go out of the sanctuary; for thou hast trespassed; neither <i>shall it be</i>
        for thine honour from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Uzziah was wroth, and <i>had</i> a censer in his hand to burn
        incense: and while he was wroth with the priests, the leprosy even rose up
        in his forehead before the priests in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        from beside the incense altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Azariah the chief priest, and all the priests, looked upon him,
        and, behold, he <i>was</i> leprous in his forehead, and they thrust him out
        from thence; yea, himself hasted also to go out, because the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        had smitten him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Uzziah the king was a leper unto the day of his death, and dwelt
        in a several house, <i>being</i> a leper; for he was cut off from the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: and Jotham his son <i>was</i> over the
        king''s house, judging the people of the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Uzziah, first and last, did Isaiah the
        prophet, the son of Amoz, write. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So Uzziah slept with his fathers, and they buried him with his fathers
        in the field of the burial which <i>belonged</i> to the kings; for they said,
        He <i>is</i> a leper: and Jotham his son reigned in his stead.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jotham'
      title: Jotham
      number: 1
      content: '  Jotham <i>was</i> twenty and five years old when he began to reign,
        and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name also <i>was</i>
        Jerushah, the daughter of Zadok. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did <i>that which was</i> right in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        according to all that his father Uzziah did: howbeit he entered not into
        the temple of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. And the people did yet corruptly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He built the high gate of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and on the wall of Ophel he built much. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Moreover he built cities in the mountains of Judah, and in the forests
        he built castles and towers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He fought also with the king of the Ammonites, and prevailed against
        them. And the children of Ammon gave him the same year an hundred talents
        of silver, and ten thousand measures of wheat, and ten thousand of barley.
        So much did the children of Ammon pay unto him, both the second year, and
        the third. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jotham became mighty, because he prepared his ways before the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all his wars, and his ways,
        lo, they <i>are</i> written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He was five and twenty years old when he began to reign, and reigned
        sixteen years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Jotham slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city
        of David: and Ahaz his son reigned in his stead.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaz'
      title: Ahaz
      number: 1
      content: '  Ahaz <i>was</i> twenty years old when he began to reign, and he
        reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem: but he did not <i>that which was</i>
        right in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, like David his father: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'for he walked in the ways of the kings of Israel, and made also molten
        images for Baalim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Moreover he burnt incense in the valley of the son of Hinnom, and
        burnt his children in the fire, after the abominations of the heathen whom
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had cast out before the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He sacrificed also and burnt incense in the high places, and on the
        hills, and under every green tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Wherefore the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God delivered him into
        the hand of the king of Syria; and they smote him, and carried away a great
        multitude of them captives, and brought <i>them</i> to Damascus. And he was
        also delivered into the hand of the king of Israel, who smote him with a
        great slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For Pekah the son of Remaliah slew in Judah an hundred and twenty
        thousand in one day, <i>which were</i> all valiant men; because they had
        forsaken the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Zichri, a mighty man of Ephraim, slew Maaseiah the king''s son,
        and Azrikam the governor of the house, and Elkanah <i>that was</i> next to
        the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the children of Israel carried away captive of their brethren
        two hundred thousand, women, sons, and daughters, and took also away much
        spoil from them, and brought the spoil to Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But a prophet of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> was there, whose
        name <i>was</i> Oded: and he went out before the host that came to Samaria,
        and said unto them, Behold, because the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of
        your fathers was wroth with Judah, he hath delivered them into your hand,
        and ye have slain them in a rage <i>that</i> reacheth up unto heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now ye purpose to keep under the children of Judah and Jerusalem
        for bondmen and bondwomen unto you: <i>but are there</i> not with you, even
        with you, sins against the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> your God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now hear me therefore, and deliver the captives again, which ye have
        taken captive of your brethren: for the fierce wrath of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>is</i> upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then certain of the heads of the children of Ephraim, Azariah the
        son of Johanan, Berechiah the son of Meshillemoth, and Jehizkiah the son
        of Shallum, and Amasa the son of Hadlai, stood up against them that came
        from the war, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and said unto them, Ye shall not bring in the captives hither: for
        whereas we have offended against the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>already</i>,
        ye intend to add <i>more</i> to our sins and to our trespass: for our trespass
        is great, and <i>there is</i> fierce wrath against Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the armed men left the captives and the spoil before the princes
        and all the congregation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the men which were expressed by name rose up, and took the captives,
        and with the spoil clothed all that were naked among them, and arrayed them,
        and shod them, and gave them to eat and to drink, and anointed them, and
        carried all the feeble of them upon asses, and brought them to Jericho, the
        city of palm trees, to their brethren: then they returned to Samaria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'At that time did king Ahaz send unto the kings of Assyria to help
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For again the Edomites had come and smitten Judah, and carried away
        captives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Philistines also had invaded the cities of the low country, and
        of the south of Judah, and had taken Beth-shemesh, and Ajalon, and Gederoth,
        and Shocho with the villages thereof, and Timnah with the villages thereof,
        Gimzo also and the villages thereof: and they dwelt there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> brought Judah low because of
        Ahaz king of Israel; for he made Judah naked, and transgressed sore against
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria came unto him, and distressed
        him, but strengthened him not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For Ahaz took away a portion <i>out</i> of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and <i>out</i> of the house of the king, and of the princes, and gave <i>it</i>
        unto the king of Assyria: but he helped him not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And in the time of his distress did he trespass yet more against
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: this <i>is that</i> king Ahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For he sacrificed unto the gods of Damascus, which smote him: and
        he said, Because the gods of the kings of Syria help them, <i>therefore</i>
        will I sacrifice to them, that they may help me. But they were the ruin of
        him, and of all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Ahaz gathered together the vessels of the house of God, and cut
        in pieces the vessels of the house of God, and shut up the doors of the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and he made him altars in every corner
        of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And in every several city of Judah he made high places to burn incense
        unto other gods, and provoked to anger the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God
        of his fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of his acts and of all his ways, first and last, behold,
        they <i>are</i> written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Ahaz slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city,
        <i>even</i> in Jerusalem: but they brought him not into the sepulchres of
        the kings of Israel: and Hezekiah his son reigned in his stead.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah'
      title: Hezekiah
      number: 1
      content: '  Hezekiah began to reign <i>when he was</i> five and twenty years
        old, and he reigned nine and twenty years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s
        name <i>was</i> Abijah, the daughter of Zechariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did <i>that which was</i> right in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        according to all that David his father had done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He in the first year of his reign, in the first month, opened the
        doors of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and repaired them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he brought in the priests and the Levites, and gathered them
        together into the east street, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and said unto them, Hear me, ye Levites, sanctify now yourselves,
        and sanctify the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of your fathers,
        and carry forth the filthiness out of the holy <i>place</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For our fathers have trespassed, and done <i>that which was</i> evil
        in the eyes of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> our God, and have forsaken
        him, and have turned away their faces from the habitation of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and turned <i>their</i> backs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Also they have shut up the doors of the porch, and put out the lamps,
        and have not burned incense nor offered burnt offerings in the holy <i>place</i>
        unto the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Wherefore the wrath of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> was upon Judah
        and Jerusalem, and he hath delivered them to trouble, to astonishment, and
        to hissing, as ye see with your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For, lo, our fathers have fallen by the sword, and our sons and our
        daughters and our wives <i>are</i> in captivity for this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now <i>it is</i> in mine heart to make a covenant with the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel, that his fierce wrath may turn away from us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My sons, be not now negligent: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath chosen you to stand before him, to serve him, and that ye should minister
        unto him, and burn incense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the Levites arose, Mahath the son of Amasai, and Joel the son
        of Azariah, of the sons of the Kohathites: and of the sons of Merari, Kish
        the son of Abdi, and Azariah the son of Jehalelel: and of the Gershonites;
        Joah the son of Zimmah, and Eden the son of Joah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and of the sons of Elizaphan; Shimri, and Jeiel: and of the sons
        of Asaph; Zechariah, and Mattaniah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and of the sons of Heman; Jehiel, and Shimei: and of the sons of
        Jeduthun; Shemaiah, and Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Cleansed the Temple'
      title: Cleansed the Temple
      number: 15
      content: 'And they gathered their brethren, and sanctified themselves, and
        came, according to the commandment of the king, by the words of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        to cleanse the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the priests went into the inner part of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        to cleanse <i>it</i>, and brought out all the uncleanness that they found
        in the temple of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> into the court of the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. And the Levites took <i>it</i>, to carry
        <i>it</i> out abroad into the brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now they began on the first <i>day</i> of the first month to sanctify,
        and on the eighth day of the month came they to the porch of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        so they sanctified the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> in eight
        days; and in the sixteenth day of the first month they made an end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then they went in to Hezekiah the king, and said, We have cleansed
        all the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and the altar of burnt
        offering, with all the vessels thereof, and the shewbread table, with all
        the vessels thereof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Moreover all the vessels, which king Ahaz in his reign did cast away
        in his transgression, have we prepared and sanctified, and, behold, they
        <i>are</i> before the altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Hezekiah the king rose early, and gathered the rulers of the
        city, and went up to the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they brought seven bullocks, and seven rams, and seven lambs,
        and seven he goats, for a sin offering for the kingdom, and for the sanctuary,
        and for Judah. And he commanded the priests the sons of Aaron to offer <i>them</i>
        on the altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So they killed the bullocks, and the priests received the blood,
        and sprinkled <i>it</i> on the altar: likewise, when they had killed the
        rams, they sprinkled the blood upon the altar: they killed also the lambs,
        and they sprinkled the blood upon the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they brought forth the he goats <i>for</i> the sin offering before
        the king and the congregation; and they laid their hands upon them: '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and the priests killed them, and they made reconciliation with their
        blood upon the altar, to make an atonement for all Israel: for the king commanded
        <i>that</i> the burnt offering and the sin offering <i>should be made</i>
        for all Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And he set the Levites in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        with cymbals, with psalteries, and with harps, according to the commandment
        of David, and of Gad the king''s seer, and Nathan the prophet: for <i>so
        was</i> the commandment of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> by his prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And the Levites stood with the instruments of David, and the priests
        with the trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Hezekiah commanded to offer the burnt offering upon the altar.
        And when the burnt offering began, the song of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        began <i>also</i> with the trumpets, and with the instruments <i>ordained</i>
        by David king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And all the congregation worshipped, and the singers sang, and the
        trumpeters sounded: <i>and</i> all <i>this continued</i> until the burnt
        offering was finished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And when they had made an end of offering, the king and all that
        were present with him bowed themselves, and worshipped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Moreover Hezekiah the king and the princes commanded the Levites
        to sing praise unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> with the words of David,
        and of Asaph the seer. And they sang praises with gladness, and they bowed
        their heads and worshipped.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then Hezekiah answered and said, Now ye have consecrated yourselves
        unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, come near and bring sacrifices and
        thank offerings into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. And the
        congregation brought in sacrifices and thank offerings; and as many as were
        of a free heart burnt offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the number of the burnt offerings, which the congregation brought,
        was threescore and ten bullocks, an hundred rams, <i>and</i> two hundred
        lambs: all these <i>were</i> for a burnt offering to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the consecrated things <i>were</i> six hundred oxen and three
        thousand sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But the priests were too few, so that they could not flay all the
        burnt offerings: wherefore their brethren the Levites did help them, till
        the work was ended, and until the <i>other</i> priests had sanctified themselves:
        for the Levites <i>were</i> more upright in heart to sanctify themselves
        than the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And also the burnt offerings <i>were</i> in abundance, with the fat
        of the peace offerings, and the drink offerings for <i>every</i> burnt offering.
        So the service of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> was set in
        order. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And Hezekiah rejoiced, and all the people, that God had prepared
        the people: for the thing was <i>done</i> suddenly.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Renewed the Passover'
      title: Renewed the Passover
      number: 1
      content: '  And Hezekiah sent to all Israel and Judah, and wrote letters also
        to Ephraim and Manasseh, that they should come to the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        at Jerusalem, to keep the passover unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the king had taken counsel, and his princes, and all the congregation
        in Jerusalem, to keep the passover in the second month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For they could not keep it at that time, because the priests had
        not sanctified themselves sufficiently, neither had the people gathered themselves
        together to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the thing pleased the king and all the congregation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So they established a decree to make proclamation throughout all
        Israel, from Beer-sheba even to Dan, that they should come to keep the passover
        unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel at Jerusalem: for they
        had not done <i>it</i> of a long <i>time in such sort</i> as it was written. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the posts went with the letters from the king and his princes
        throughout all Israel and Judah, and according to the commandment of the
        king, saying, Ye children of Israel, turn again unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, and he will return to the remnant of you,
        that are escaped out of the hand of the kings of Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And be not ye like your fathers, and like your brethren, which trespassed
        against the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of their fathers, <i>who</i>
        therefore gave them up to desolation, as ye see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now be ye not stiffnecked, as your fathers <i>were, but</i> yield
        yourselves unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and enter into his sanctuary,
        which he hath sanctified for ever: and serve the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        your God, that the fierceness of his wrath may turn away from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For if ye turn again unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, your brethren
        and your children <i>shall find</i> compassion before them that lead them
        captive, so that they shall come again into this land: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        your God <i>is</i> gracious and merciful, and will not turn away <i>his</i>
        face from you, if ye return unto him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the posts passed from city to city through the country of Ephraim
        and Manasseh, even unto Zebulun: but they laughed them to scorn, and mocked
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Nevertheless divers of Asher and Manasseh and of Zebulun humbled
        themselves, and came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Also in Judah the hand of God was to give them one heart to do the
        commandment of the king and of the princes, by the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And there assembled at Jerusalem much people to keep the feast of
        unleavened bread in the second month, a very great congregation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they arose and took away the altars that <i>were</i> in Jerusalem,
        and all the altars for incense took they away, and cast <i>them</i> into
        the brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then they killed the passover on the fourteenth <i>day</i> of the
        second month: and the priests and the Levites were ashamed, and sanctified
        themselves, and brought in the burnt offerings into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And they stood in their place after their manner, according to the
        law of Moses the man of God: the priests sprinkled the blood, <i>which they
        received</i> of the hand of the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For <i>there were</i> many in the congregation that were not sanctified:
        therefore the Levites had the charge of the killing of the passovers for
        every one <i>that was</i> not clean, to sanctify <i>them</i> unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For a multitude of the people, <i>even</i> many of Ephraim, and Manasseh,
        Issachar, and Zebulun, had not cleansed themselves, yet did they eat the
        passover otherwise than it was written. But Hezekiah prayed for them, saying,
        The good <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> pardon every one '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<i>that</i> prepareth his heart to seek God, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of his fathers, though <i>he be</i> not <i>cleansed</i> according to
        the purification of the sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hearkened to Hezekiah, and healed
        the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the children of Israel that were present at Jerusalem kept the
        feast of unleavened bread seven days with great gladness: and the Levites
        and the priests praised the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> day by day, <i>singing</i>
        with loud instruments unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Hezekiah spake comfortably unto all the Levites that taught the
        good knowledge of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: and they did eat throughout
        the feast seven days, offering peace offerings, and making confession to
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the whole assembly took counsel to keep other seven days: and
        they kept <i>other</i> seven days with gladness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For Hezekiah king of Judah did give to the congregation a thousand
        bullocks and seven thousand sheep; and the princes gave to the congregation
        a thousand bullocks and ten thousand sheep: and a great number of priests
        sanctified themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And all the congregation of Judah, with the priests and the Levites,
        and all the congregation that came out of Israel, and the strangers that
        came out of the land of Israel, and that dwelt in Judah, rejoiced. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So there was great joy in Jerusalem: for since the time of Solomon
        the son of David king of Israel <i>there was</i> not the like in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then the priests the Levites arose and blessed the people: and their
        voice was heard, and their prayer came <i>up</i> to his holy dwelling place,
        <i>even</i> unto heaven.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when all this was finished, all Israel that were present went
        out to the cities of Judah, and brake the images in pieces, and cut down
        the groves, and threw down the high places and the altars out of all Judah
        and Benjamin, in Ephraim also and Manasseh, until they had utterly destroyed
        them all. Then all the children of Israel returned, every man to his possession,
        into their own cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Hezekiah appointed the courses of the priests and the Levites
        after their courses, every man according to his service, the priests and
        Levites for burnt offerings and for peace offerings, to minister, and to
        give thanks, and to praise in the gates of the tents of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<i>He appointed</i> also the king''s portion of his substance for
        the burnt offerings, <i>to wit</i>, for the morning and evening burnt offerings,
        and the burnt offerings for the sabbaths, and for the new moons, and for
        the set feasts, as <i>it is</i> written in the law of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Encouraged the People'
      title: Encouraged the People
      number: 4
      content: 'Moreover he commanded the people that dwelt in Jerusalem to give
        the portion of the priests and the Levites, that they might be encouraged
        in the law of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And as soon as the commandment came abroad, the children of Israel
        brought in abundance the firstfruits of corn, wine, and oil, and honey, and
        of all the increase of the field; and the tithe of all <i>things</i> brought
        they in abundantly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And <i>concerning</i> the children of Israel and Judah, that dwelt
        in the cities of Judah, they also brought in the tithe of oxen and sheep,
        and the tithe of holy things which were consecrated unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        their God, and laid <i>them</i> by heaps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In the third month they began to lay the foundation of the heaps,
        and finished <i>them</i> in the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when Hezekiah and the princes came and saw the heaps, they blessed
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and his people Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Hezekiah questioned with the priests and the Levites concerning
        the heaps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Azariah the chief priest of the house of Zadok answered him,
        and said, Since <i>the people</i> began to bring the offerings into the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, we have had enough to eat, and have left
        plenty: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath blessed his people; and
        that which is left <i>is</i> this great store.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Hezekiah commanded to prepare chambers in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        and they prepared <i>them</i>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and brought in the offerings and the tithes and the dedicated <i>things</i>
        faithfully: over which Cononiah the Levite <i>was</i> ruler, and Shimei his
        brother <i>was</i> the next. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Jehiel, and Azaziah, and Nahath, and Asahel, and Jerimoth, and
        Jozabad, and Eliel, and Ismachiah, and Mahath, and Benaiah, <i>were</i> overseers
        under the hand of Cononiah and Shimei his brother, at the commandment of
        Hezekiah the king, and Azariah the ruler of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Kore the son of Imnah the Levite, the porter toward the east,
        <i>was</i> over the freewill offerings of God, to distribute the oblations
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and the most holy things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And next him <i>were</i> Eden, and Miniamin, and Jeshua, and Shemaiah,
        Amariah, and Shecaniah, in the cities of the priests, in <i>their</i> set
        office, to give to their brethren by courses, as well to the great as to
        the small: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'beside their genealogy of males, from three years old and upward,
        <i>even</i> unto every one that entereth into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        his daily portion for their service in their charges according to their courses; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'both to the genealogy of the priests by the house of their fathers,
        and the Levites from twenty years old and upward, in their charges by their
        courses; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and to the genealogy of all their little ones, their wives, and their
        sons, and their daughters, through all the congregation: for in their set
        office they sanctified themselves in holiness: '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'also of the sons of Aaron the priests, <i>which were</i> in the fields
        of the suburbs of their cities, in every several city, the men that were
        expressed by name, to give portions to all the males among the priests, and
        to all that were reckoned by genealogies among the Levites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And thus did Hezekiah throughout all Judah, and wrought <i>that which
        was</i> good and right and truth before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And in every work that he began in the service of the house of God,
        and in the law, and in the commandments, to seek his God, he did <i>it</i>
        with all his heart, and prospered.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem Threatened'
      title: Jerusalem Threatened
      number: 1
      content: '  After these things, and the establishment thereof, Sennacherib
        king of Assyria came, and entered into Judah, and encamped against the fenced
        cities, and thought to win them for himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when Hezekiah saw that Sennacherib was come, and that he was
        purposed to fight against Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'he took counsel with his princes and his mighty men to stop the waters
        of the fountains which <i>were</i> without the city: and they did help him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So there was gathered much people together, who stopped all the fountains,
        and the brook that ran through the midst of the land, saying, Why should
        the kings of Assyria come, and find much water? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Also he strengthened himself, and built up all the wall that was
        broken, and raised <i>it</i> up to the towers, and another wall without,
        and repaired Millo <i>in</i> the city of David, and made darts and shields
        in abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he set captains of war over the people, and gathered them together
        to him in the street of the gate of the city, and spake comfortably to them,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Be strong and courageous, be not afraid nor dismayed for the king
        of Assyria, nor for all the multitude that <i>is</i> with him: for <i>there
        be</i> more with us than with him: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'with him <i>is</i> an arm of flesh; but with us <i>is</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        our God to help us, and to fight our battles. And the people rested themselves
        upon the words of Hezekiah king of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'After this did Sennacherib king of Assyria send his servants to Jerusalem,
        (but he <i>himself laid siege</i> against Lachish, and all his power with
        him,) unto Hezekiah king of Judah, and unto all Judah that <i>were</i> at
        Jerusalem, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Thus saith Sennacherib king of Assyria, Whereon do ye trust, that
        ye abide in the siege in Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Doth not Hezekiah persuade you to give over yourselves to die by
        famine and by thirst, saying, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> our God shall
        deliver us out of the hand of the king of Assyria? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Hath not the same Hezekiah taken away his high places and his altars,
        and commanded Judah and Jerusalem, saying, Ye shall worship before one altar,
        and burn incense upon it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Know ye not what I and my fathers have done unto all the people of
        <i>other</i> lands? were the gods of the nations of those lands any ways
        able to deliver their lands out of mine hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who <i>was there</i> among all the gods of those nations that my
        fathers utterly destroyed, that could deliver his people out of mine hand,
        that your God should be able to deliver you out of mine hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now therefore let not Hezekiah deceive you, nor persuade you on this
        manner, neither yet believe him: for no god of any nation or kingdom was
        able to deliver his people out of mine hand, and out of the hand of my fathers:
        how much less shall your God deliver you out of mine hand?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And his servants spake yet <i>more</i> against the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God, and against his servant Hezekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He wrote also letters to rail on the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel, and to speak against him, saying, As the gods of the nations
        of <i>other</i> lands have not delivered their people out of mine hand, so
        shall not the God of Hezekiah deliver his people out of mine hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then they cried with a loud voice in the Jews'' speech unto the people
        of Jerusalem that <i>were</i> on the wall, to affright them, and to trouble
        them; that they might take the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And they spake against the God of Jerusalem, as against the gods
        of the people of the earth, <i>which were</i> the work of the hands of man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Jerusalem Delivered'
      title: Jerusalem Delivered
      number: 20
      content: 'And for this <i>cause</i> Hezekiah the king, and the prophet Isaiah
        the son of Amoz, prayed and cried to heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> sent an angel, which cut off
        all the mighty men of valour, and the leaders and captains in the camp of
        the king of Assyria. So he returned with shame of face to his own land. And
        when he was come into the house of his god, they that came forth of his own
        bowels slew him there with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Thus the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> saved Hezekiah and the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem from the hand of Sennacherib the king of Assyria, and from the
        hand of all <i>other</i>, and guided them on every side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And many brought gifts unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> to Jerusalem,
        and presents to Hezekiah king of Judah: so that he was magnified in the sight
        of all nations from thenceforth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'In those days Hezekiah was sick to the death, and prayed unto the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: and he spake unto him, and he gave him a sign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But Hezekiah rendered not again according to the benefit <i>done</i>
        unto him; for his heart was lifted up: therefore there was wrath upon him,
        and upon Judah and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Notwithstanding Hezekiah humbled himself for the pride of his heart,
        <i>both</i> he and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that the wrath of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came not upon them in the days of Hezekiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Hezekiah had exceeding much riches and honour: and he made himself
        treasuries for silver, and for gold, and for precious stones, and for spices,
        and for shields, and for all manner of pleasant jewels; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'storehouses also for the increase of corn, and wine, and oil; and
        stalls for all manner of beasts, and cotes for flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Moreover he provided him cities, and possessions of flocks and herds
        in abundance: for God had given him substance very much. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'This same Hezekiah also stopped the upper watercourse of Gihon, and
        brought it straight down to the west side of the city of David. And Hezekiah
        prospered in all his works. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Howbeit in <i>the business of</i> the ambassadors of the princes
        of Babylon, who sent unto him to enquire of the wonder that was <i>done</i>
        in the land, God left him, to try him, that he might know all <i>that was</i>
        in his heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah, and his goodness, behold, they
        <i>are</i> written in the vision of Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz,
        <i>and</i> in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And Hezekiah slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the chiefest
        of the sepulchres of the sons of David: and all Judah and the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem did him honour at his death. And Manasseh his son reigned in
        his stead.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Manasseh'
      title: Manasseh
      number: 1
      content: '  Manasseh <i>was</i> twelve years old when he began to reign, and
        he reigned fifty and five years in Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'but did <i>that which was</i> evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        like unto the abominations of the heathen, whom the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        had cast out before the children of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For he built again the high places which Hezekiah his father had
        broken down, and he reared up altars for Baalim, and made groves, and worshipped
        all the host of heaven, and served them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Also he built altars in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        whereof the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had said, In Jerusalem shall my name
        be for ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courts
        of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he caused his children to pass through the fire in the valley
        of the son of Hinnom: also he observed times, and used enchantments, and
        used witchcraft, and dealt with a familiar spirit, and with wizards: he wrought
        much evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, to provoke him
        to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he set a carved image, the idol which he had made, in the house
        of God, of which God had said to David and to Solomon his son, In this house,
        and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen before all the tribes of Israel, will
        I put my name for ever: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'neither will I any more remove the foot of Israel from out of the
        land which I have appointed for your fathers; so that they will take heed
        to do all that I have commanded them, according to the whole law and the
        statutes and the ordinances by the hand of Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Manasseh made Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to err, <i>and</i>
        to do worse than the heathen, whom the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had destroyed
        before the children of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> spake to Manasseh, and to his
        people: but they would not hearken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Wherefore the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> brought upon them the captains
        of the host of the king of Assyria, which took Manasseh among the thorns,
        and bound him with fetters, and carried him to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when he was in affliction, he besought the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        his God, and humbled himself greatly before the God of his fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and prayed unto him: and he was intreated of him, and heard his supplication,
        and brought him again to Jerusalem into his kingdom. Then Manasseh knew that
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> he <i>was</i> God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now after this he built a wall without the city of David, on the
        west side of Gihon, in the valley, even to the entering in at the fish gate,
        and compassed about Ophel, and raised it up a very great height, and put
        captains of war in all the fenced cities of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he took away the strange gods, and the idol out of the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and all the altars that he had built
        in the mount of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and in Jerusalem,
        and cast <i>them</i> out of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he repaired the altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and
        sacrificed thereon peace offerings and thank offerings, and commanded Judah
        to serve the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Nevertheless the people did sacrifice still in the high places, <i>yet</i>
        unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> their God only.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh, and his prayer unto his God,
        and the words of the seers that spake to him in the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel, behold, they <i>are written</i> in the book of the kings of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'His prayer also, and <i>how God</i> was intreated of him, and all
        his sins, and his trespass, and the places wherein he built high places,
        and set up groves and graven images, before he was humbled: behold, they
        <i>are</i> written among the sayings of the seers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Amon'
      title: Amon
      number: 20
      content: 'So Manasseh slept with his fathers, and they buried him in his own
        house: and Amon his son reigned in his stead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Amon <i>was</i> two and twenty years old when he began to reign,
        and reigned two years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But he did <i>that which was</i> evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        as did Manasseh his father: for Amon sacrificed unto all the carved images
        which Manasseh his father had made, and served them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and humbled not himself before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, as
        Manasseh his father had humbled himself; but Amon trespassed more and more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And his servants conspired against him, and slew him in his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: But the people of the land slew all them that had conspired against
        king Amon; and the people of the land made Josiah his son king in his stead.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Josiah'
      title: Josiah
      number: 1
      content: '  Josiah <i>was</i> eight years old when he began to reign, and he
        reigned in Jerusalem one and thirty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did <i>that which was</i> right in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and walked in the ways of David his father, and declined <i>neither</i> to
        the right hand, nor to the left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For in the eighth year of his reign, while he was yet young, he began
        to seek after the God of David his father: and in the twelfth year he began
        to purge Judah and Jerusalem from the high places, and the groves, and the
        carved images, and the molten images. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they brake down the altars of Baalim in his presence; and the
        images, that <i>were</i> on high above them, he cut down; and the groves,
        and the carved images, and the molten images, he brake in pieces, and made
        dust <i>of them</i>, and strowed <i>it</i> upon the graves of them that had
        sacrificed unto them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he burnt the bones of the priests upon their altars, and cleansed
        Judah and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And <i>so did he</i> in the cities of Manasseh, and Ephraim, and
        Simeon, even unto Naphtali, with their mattocks round about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when he had broken down the altars and the groves, and had beaten
        the graven images into powder, and cut down all the idols throughout all
        the land of Israel, he returned to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now in the eighteenth year of his reign, when he had purged the land,
        and the house, he sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah, and Maaseiah the governor
        of the city, and Joah the son of Joahaz the recorder, to repair the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when they came to Hilkiah the high priest, they delivered the
        money that was brought into the house of God, which the Levites that kept
        the doors had gathered of the hand of Manasseh and Ephraim, and of all the
        remnant of Israel, and of all Judah and Benjamin; and they returned to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they put <i>it</i> in the hand of the workmen that had the oversight
        of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and they gave it to the
        workmen that wrought in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, to
        repair and amend the house: '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'even to the artificers and builders gave they <i>it</i>, to buy hewn
        stone, and timber for couplings, and to floor the houses which the kings
        of Judah had destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the men did the work faithfully: and the overseers of them <i>were</i>
        Jahath and Obadiah, the Levites, of the sons of Merari; and Zechariah and
        Meshullam, of the sons of the Kohathites, to set <i>it</i> forward; and <i>other
        of</i> the Levites, all that could skill of instruments of musick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Book of the Law Found'
      title: The Book of the Law Found
      number: 13
      content: 'Also <i>they were</i> over the bearers of burdens, and <i>were</i>
        overseers of all that wrought the work in any manner of service: and of the
        Levites <i>there were</i> scribes, and officers, and porters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when they brought out the money that was brought into the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Hilkiah the priest found a book of the
        law of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>given</i> by Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Hilkiah answered and said to Shaphan the scribe, I have found
        the book of the law in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. And
        Hilkiah delivered the book to Shaphan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Shaphan carried the book to the king, and brought the king word
        back again, saying, All that was committed to thy servants, they do <i>it</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they have gathered together the money that was found in the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and have delivered it into the hand of
        the overseers, and to the hand of the workmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Shaphan the scribe told the king, saying, Hilkiah the priest
        hath given me a book. And Shaphan read it before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And it came to pass, when the king had heard the words of the law,
        that he rent his clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the king commanded Hilkiah, and Ahikam the son of Shaphan, and
        Abdon the son of Micah, and Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah a servant of the
        king''s, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Go, enquire of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> for me, and for them
        that are left in Israel and in Judah, concerning the words of the book that
        is found: for great <i>is</i> the wrath of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        that is poured out upon us, because our fathers have not kept the word of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, to do after all that is written in this
        book.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Hilkiah, and <i>they</i> that the king <i>had appointed</i>,
        went to Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tikvath, the
        son of Hasrah, keeper of the wardrobe; (now she dwelt in Jerusalem in the
        college:) and they spake to her to that <i>effect</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And she answered them, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel, Tell ye the man that sent you to me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Behold, I will bring
        evil upon this place, and upon the inhabitants thereof, <i>even</i> all the
        curses that are written in the book which they have read before the king
        of Judah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'because they have forsaken me, and have burned incense unto other
        gods, that they might provoke me to anger with all the works of their hands;
        therefore my wrath shall be poured out upon this place, and shall not be
        quenched. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And as for the king of Judah, who sent you to enquire of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        so shall ye say unto him, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God
        of Israel <i>concerning</i> the words which thou hast heard; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'because thine heart was tender, and thou didst humble thyself before
        God, when thou heardest his words against this place, and against the inhabitants
        thereof, and humbledst thyself before me, and didst rend thy clothes, and
        weep before me; I have even heard <i>thee</i> also, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: The Covenant Renewed'
      title: The Covenant Renewed
      number: 28
      content: 'Behold, I will gather thee to thy fathers, and thou shalt be gathered
        to thy grave in peace, neither shall thine eyes see all the evil that I will
        bring upon this place, and upon the inhabitants of the same. So they brought
        the king word again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the king sent and gathered together all the elders of Judah
        and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the king went up into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and all the men of Judah, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and the priests,
        and the Levites, and all the people, great and small: and he read in their
        ears all the words of the book of the covenant that was found in the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And the king stood in his place, and made a covenant before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        to walk after the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and to keep his commandments,
        and his testimonies, and his statutes, with all his heart, and with all his
        soul, to perform the words of the covenant which are written in this book. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he caused all that were present in Jerusalem and Benjamin to
        stand <i>to it</i>. And the inhabitants of Jerusalem did according to the
        covenant of God, the God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: And Josiah took away all the abominations out of all the countries
        that <i>pertained</i> to the children of Israel, and made all that were present
        in Israel to serve, <i>even</i> to serve the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        their God. <i>And</i> all his days they departed not from following the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        the God of their fathers.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Moreover Josiah kept a passover unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        in Jerusalem: and they killed the passover on the fourteenth <i>day</i> of
        the first month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he set the priests in their charges, and encouraged them to the
        service of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and said unto the Levites that taught all Israel, which were holy
        unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Put the holy ark in the house which
        Solomon the son of David king of Israel did build; <i>it shall</i> not <i>be</i>
        a burden upon <i>your</i> shoulders: serve now the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        your God, and his people Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and prepare <i>yourselves</i> by the houses of your fathers, after
        your courses, according to the writing of David king of Israel, and according
        to the writing of Solomon his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And stand in the holy <i>place</i> according to the divisions of
        the families of the fathers of your brethren the people, and <i>after</i>
        the division of the families of the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So kill the passover, and sanctify yourselves, and prepare your brethren,
        that <i>they</i> may do according to the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        by the hand of Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Josiah gave to the people, of the flock, lambs and kids, all
        for the passover offerings, for all that were present, to the number of thirty
        thousand, and three thousand bullocks: these <i>were</i> of the king''s substance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And his princes gave willingly unto the people, to the priests, and
        to the Levites: Hilkiah and Zechariah and Jehiel, rulers of the house of
        God, gave unto the priests for the passover offerings two thousand and six
        hundred <i>small cattle</i>, and three hundred oxen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Conaniah also, and Shemaiah and Nethaneel, his brethren, and Hashabiah
        and Jeiel and Jozabad, chief of the Levites, gave unto the Levites for passover
        offerings five thousand <i>small cattle</i>, and five hundred oxen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the service was prepared, and the priests stood in their place,
        and the Levites in their courses, according to the king''s commandment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they killed the passover, and the priests sprinkled <i>the blood</i>
        from their hands, and the Levites flayed <i>them</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they removed the burnt offerings, that they might give according
        to the divisions of the families of the people, to offer unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        as <i>it is</i> written in the book of Moses. And so <i>did they</i> with
        the oxen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And they roasted the passover with fire according to the ordinance:
        but the <i>other</i> holy <i>offerings</i> sod they in pots, and in caldrons,
        and in pans, and divided <i>them</i> speedily among all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And afterward they made ready for themselves, and for the priests:
        because the priests the sons of Aaron <i>were busied</i> in offering of burnt
        offerings and the fat until night; therefore the Levites prepared for themselves,
        and for the priests the sons of Aaron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the singers the sons of Asaph <i>were</i> in their place, according
        to the commandment of David, and Asaph, and Heman, and Jeduthun the king''s
        seer; and the porters <i>waited</i> at every gate; they might not depart
        from their service; for their brethren the Levites prepared for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So all the service of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> was prepared
        the same day, to keep the passover, and to offer burnt offerings upon the
        altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, according to the commandment of
        king Josiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the children of Israel that were present kept the passover at
        that time, and the feast of unleavened bread seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And there was no passover like to that kept in Israel from the days
        of Samuel the prophet; neither did all the kings of Israel keep such a passover
        as Josiah kept, and the priests, and the Levites, and all Judah and Israel
        that were present, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Death of Josiah'
      title: Death of Josiah
      number: 19
      content: 'In the eighteenth year of the reign of Josiah was this passover kept.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After all this, when Josiah had prepared the temple, Necho king of
        Egypt came up to fight against Carchemish by Euphrates: and Josiah went out
        against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But he sent ambassadors to him, saying, What have I to do with thee,
        thou king of Judah? <i>I come</i> not against thee this day, but against
        the house wherewith I have war: for God commanded me to make haste: forbear
        thee from <i>meddling with</i> God, who <i>is</i> with me, that he destroy
        thee not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Nevertheless Josiah would not turn his face from him, but disguised
        himself, that he might fight with him, and hearkened not unto the words of
        Necho from the mouth of God, and came to fight in the valley of Megiddo. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the archers shot at king Josiah; and the king said to his servants,
        Have me away; for I am sore wounded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'His servants therefore took him out of that chariot, and put him
        in the second chariot that he had; and they brought him to Jerusalem, and
        he died, and was buried in <i>one of</i> the sepulchres of his fathers. And
        all Judah and Jerusalem mourned for Josiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Jeremiah lamented for Josiah: and all the singing men and the
        singing women spake of Josiah in their lamentations to this day, and made
        them an ordinance in Israel: and, behold, they <i>are</i> written in the
        lamentations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Josiah, and his goodness, according to
        <i>that which was</i> written in the law of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: and his deeds, first and last, behold, they <i>are</i> written in
        the book of the kings of Israel and Judah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Under Egypt'
      title: Under Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the people of the land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah, and
        made him king in his father''s stead in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jehoahaz <i>was</i> twenty and three years old when he began to reign,
        and he reigned three months in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the king of Egypt put him down at Jerusalem, and condemned the
        land in an hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Attacked by Babylon'
      title: Attacked by Babylon
      number: 4
      content: 'And the king of Egypt made Eliakim his brother king over Judah and
        Jerusalem, and turned his name to Jehoiakim. And Necho took Jehoahaz his
        brother, and carried him to Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Jehoiakim <i>was</i> twenty and five years old when he began to reign,
        and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem: and he did <i>that which was</i>
        evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Against him came up Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and bound him
        in fetters, to carry him to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nebuchadnezzar also carried of the vessels of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        to Babylon, and put them in his temple at Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, and his abominations which
        he did, and that which was found in him, behold, they <i>are</i> written
        in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah: and Jehoiachin his son reigned
        in his stead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Jehoiachin <i>was</i> eight years old when he began to reign, and
        he reigned three months and ten days in Jerusalem: and he did <i>that which
        was</i> evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And when the year was expired, king Nebuchadnezzar sent, and brought
        him to Babylon, with the goodly vessels of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and made Zedekiah his brother king over Judah and Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Zedekiah <i>was</i> one and twenty years old when he began to reign,
        and reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he did <i>that which was</i> evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        his God, <i>and</i> humbled not himself before Jeremiah the prophet <i>speaking</i>
        from the mouth of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he also rebelled against king Nebuchadnezzar, who had made him
        swear by God: but he stiffened his neck, and hardened his heart from turning
        unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Moreover all the chief of the priests, and the people, transgressed
        very much after all the abominations of the heathen; and polluted the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> which he had hallowed in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of their fathers sent to
        them by his messengers, rising up betimes, and sending; because he had compassion
        on his people, and on his dwelling place: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Captivity'
      title: The Captivity
      number: 16
      content: 'but they mocked the messengers of God, and despised his words, and
        misused his prophets, until the wrath of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        arose against his people, till <i>there was</i> no remedy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore he brought upon them the king of the Chaldees, who slew
        their young men with the sword in the house of their sanctuary, and had no
        compassion upon young man or maiden, old man, or him that stooped for age:
        he gave <i>them</i> all into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And all the vessels of the house of God, great and small, and the
        treasures of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and the treasures
        of the king, and of his princes; all <i>these</i> he brought to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And they burnt the house of God, and brake down the wall of Jerusalem,
        and burnt all the palaces thereof with fire, and destroyed all the goodly
        vessels thereof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And them that had escaped from the sword carried he away to Babylon;
        where they were servants to him and his sons until the reign of the kingdom
        of Persia: '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Return'
      title: The Return
      number: 21
      content: 'to fulfil the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> by the mouth
        of Jeremiah, until the land had enjoyed her sabbaths: <i>for</i> as long
        as she lay desolate she kept sabbath, to fulfil threescore and ten years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, that the word of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>spoken</i> by the mouth of Jeremiah might
        be accomplished, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> stirred up the spirit of
        Cyrus king of Persia, that he made a proclamation throughout all his kingdom,
        and <i>put it</i> also in writing, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Thus saith Cyrus king of Persia, All the kingdoms of the earth hath
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of heaven given me; and he hath charged
        me to build him an house in Jerusalem, which <i>is</i> in Judah. Who <i>is
        there</i> among you of all his people? The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his
        God <i>be</i> with him, and let him go up.
